	[1153132] = L"Cut Leather: ~1_amt~ ",
	[1094913] = L"A Necromancer Shroud [Replica]",
	[1062144] = L"Click the Backup button in the <a href = \"?147\">system menu</a> of the <a href = \"?145\">house customization menu</a> to create a backup of your in-progress design.  Whenever you leave design mode without committing your new design, your in-progress design is automatically backedup.  Your house can only have one backed up design, so using this option overwrites your previous backup.  Use the <a href = \"?151\">restore</a> button to load your backed up design into your in-progress design.",
	[1062476] = L"Set Filter",
	[1153128] = L"Are you sure you wish to donate these items? ",
	[1062472] = L"You gather some of your belongings. The rest remain on the corpse.",
	[1094917] = L"Gladiator's Collar [Replica]",
	[1062148] = L"The Commit button is located in the <a href = \"?147\">system menu</a> of the <a href = \"?145\">house customization menu</a>.  Click this button to finalize your in-progress design and make it your house's active design.  See <a href = \"?165\">committing a new house design</a> for more information.",
	[1153124] = L"Sand In Ya Britches Tailor Hut",
	[1094921] = L"Warzone bonus: ~1_VALUE~ kill points",
	[1062460] = L"<CENTER>BEARD</CENTER>",
	[1062152] = L"The eyedropper tool in the <a href = \"?145\">house customization menu</a> allows you to instantly select a <a href = \"?146\">component</a> already in your house design.  Click the Eraser icon, and target the component to copy.  The component menu switches to the page where the selected component can be found, and your cursor switches to painting mode with that component active.",
