	[1151164] = L"Chronicle of the Gargoyle Queen Vol. II",
	[1026275] = L"millstone",
	[1151163] = L"As you step upon the final tile, all of the colored tiles shine brightly and a pulse of light from the pedestal temporarily blinds you. As you lower your arm from your eyes, you see that the barrier surrounding the lotus is deteriorating.  The sparkling light fades, leaving the Lotus unprotected. <br><br>\tReaching down, you delicately lift the fragile flower and admire its beauty. The petals are transparent, with a faint bluish hue and the petals voluminous and soft to the touch. Upon first glance, the lotus does indeed look as if it were carved from crystal.  The heady, intoxicating scent that rises from its petals, proves that it is, indeed, not a sculpture. It is truly sad that this is the last of its kind; a field of these must have been a glorious sight. <br><br>\tGently wrapping the lotus in some cloth, you place it in your backpack and prepare to return to the Gargoyle Queen with your prize.",
	[1026276] = L"millstone",
	[1028599] = L"palisade",
	[1026277] = L"millstone",
	[1151161] = L"You step away from the pedestal, and the barrier shines brightly, as if mocking and daring you to accept its challenge.",
	[1026278] = L"millstone",
	[1151160] = L"As you approach the pedestal, you notice the shimmering barrier protecting the beautiful lotus within.  As the Gargoyle Queen warned, this barrier covers the area surrounding the pedestal, preventing access to its treasure.  <br><br>Reaching out, you test the barrier with your weapon. The weapon does not penetrate but rather acts as if it is being pushed against a brick wall. You notice, however, that making contact with the barrier causes the colored tiles around you to come to life, their brilliant colors flashing in what seems to be a sequence. <br><br>You observe the tiles as they beautifully light up, one after the other. There seems to be a pattern to their flashing; perhaps repeating the pattern is the key to lowering the barrier? <br><br>Putting your weapon away, you watch the tiles with further detail but, after one series of flashes, they go dark.  Stepping upon the nearest tile, you see that it lights up once more upon contact. It seems that the tiles respond to touch; the pattern and the key to the barrier begins to be clear. <br><br>Shall you commence another sequence and attempt to drop the barrier?",
	[1026279] = L"millstones",
	[1151159] = L"Color Guard",
	[1026280] = L"millstones",
	[1028600] = L"nodraw",
	[1026281] = L"millstones",
	[1151157] = L"Have you killed the Lifestealers yet? Don\x2019t try my patience, or I will eat you!",
	[1026282] = L"millstones",
	[1151156] = L"You dare refuse me? You are truly an imbecile. Ah well, I guess I shall eat you, after all! Just as soon as I finish digesting my last meal, that is.",
	[1026283] = L"flour mill",
	[1151155] = L"Filthy Lifestealers!",
	[1028601] = L"nodraw",
	[1151153] = L"Indeed, you possess great knowledge of nature, mortal. You have surprised me. <br><br>\tHere, accept this strand of my hair with my blessing.  Tell the Gargoyle Queen that I wish her luck, and hope that she will see her land whole again. <br><br>\tMay the sun shine on you, mortal. Farewell.",
	[1151152] = L"It would appear that you need to improve your knowledge of nature, mortal. ",
	[1151151] = L"No? You will not gain my help without proving yourself.  If you will not do so, then apparently the Gargoyle Queen was a fool to choose you.",
	[1028602] = L"nodraw",
	[1151149] = L"Knowledge of Nature",
	[1151148] = L"        Boo, I don\x2019t like to lose! But wasn\x2019t that fun? <br><br>\tHere are some of my scales; give them to the Gargoyle Queen with my blessing and tell her she needs to come play a game with me sometime!",
	[1151147] = L"Ah ha! Looks like you are not very fast. Want to play again?",
	[1028607] = L"nodraw",
	[1151145] = L"        Oh, have you come to see me?<br><br>\tThis is wonderful! I haven\x2019t spoken to a mortal in so long.  It can get pretty droll here in the realm of dreams, and I have no one to play with! There aren\x2019t many of us left. <br><br>\tWhat\x2019s that? You want something? <br><br>\tMy scales! Ha ha! You mortals are so silly, always after something or other. <br><br>\tWell, I\x2019ll happily give you some scales if you agree to play a game with me! I love games, don\x2019t you? <br><br>\tThe game is simple:  if you can hit me 6 times, then you win!  Take this stone and step into the circle here. Then, use the stone and it will take you to my favorite place to play! <br><br>\tSo, shall we play? Excellent! Be sure to put away your pets before you teleport with me!<br>",
	[1151144] = L"Catch Me If You Can!",
	[1151143] = L"The Night Terror is no more? I see by the heart in your hand that you have felled the beast. With this final component, you have given us more than a fighting chance against the Defiler.  You have proven yourself a great and powerful ally to our people, and the Queen has asked that I provide you with this small token of appreciation.<br><br>The time for battle is nigh, my friend, and I hope that you will stand by Queen Zhah when she goes to release the Defiler. With you standing by her, I know we shall succeed!",
	[1028608] = L"nodraw",
	[1151141] = L"You have come this far and turn away now? I am disappointed in you, adventurer, as are my people. Should you regain your sense of honor, do let me know.",
	[1026291] = L"flour mill",
	[1151140] = L"The bearer of the last component will be easy to find but extremely challenging to overcome, I fear. <br><br><br>\tIn eastern Ter Mur there lies a ghost town. Formerly a fishing village, this town was long since abandoned due to the instability of the land it sits upon. Now, it is the haunting ground of a group of vile and insidious creatures:  the Night Terrors.<br><br><br>\tThe Night Terrors walk the empty streets of the village, slaying any who venture into their path.  It is the heart of one of these creatures that I require.  Journey to the village and slay one of the beasts. Once you have done so, cut it open and tear out its heart. That is the final ingredient that needed for the ritual.<br><br><br>Be careful, as the beasts are fiercely protective of one another and are extremely powerful. I look forward to your return.<br><br><br>",
	[1026292] = L"ruined bed",
	[1151139] = L"Ritual: Heart of the Night Terror",
	[1026293] = L"ruined bed",
	[502650] = L"You may not cast that on another player, because you are Young.",
	[1026294] = L"ruined bed",
	[1151137] = L"Have you solved the secret of the lotus, my friend?",
	[1026295] = L"ruined bed",
	[1151136] = L"Ritual: Pristine Crystal Lotus",
	[1026296] = L"ruined bed",
	[1151135] = L"Now, you must traverse the northern desert. On the far edge, you will find a teleporter similar to that which you took to the Athenaeum Isle.  This will take you to a barren, small, and twisted piece of land that was long ago drained by the Void. <br><br>\tThe next component will be found there: a pristine crystal lotus. Long ago, what is now desert was a beautiful field of these flowers. Sadly, the Defiler's magic drained the land of life and energy, causing the land to become the wasteland it is today. However, one bloom remains, and it is that bloom you must acquire for me.<br><br>\tIn my research, I discovered that Queen Zhah\x2019s predecessor, King Trajalem, had the only surviving bloom placed within a protective barrier on the island I am directing you to. No one knows exactly why he did so, but I have journeyed there myself and seen it with my own eyes. Unfortunately, I was not able to discern how to break the barrier protecting the lotus.<br><br>\tThe lotus stands on a pedestal surrounded by a configuration of magical tiles. I feel that these tiles are the key to breaking the barrier and obtaining the bloom.  However, their secret eluded me. What I was able to discover through research is that you must speak the words \x2018I seek the lotus\x2019 to activate the tiles.  Additionally, if you do manage to satisfy the secret of the tiles, you must state \x2018Give me the lotus.\x2019<br><br>\tJourney to the area, my friend, and please obtain the lotus. If anyone can do it, I have faith that it is you.<br><br>\tBe well, and I look forward to your return.<br><br>",
	[1026297] = L"ruined bed",
	[1005231] = L"You must use the stealing skill to pick that up.",
	[1026298] = L"ruined bed",
	[1151133] = L"Were you able to obtain the Soulbinder's Tear?",
	[1026299] = L"ruined bed",
	[1151132] = L"I fear I must now send you to convene with a creature that may not prove as willing to help as the ones you have encountered previously, my friend. I require the crystallized tear of a Soulbinder, a malevolent creature that prefers to roam the desolate edges of Ter Mur where the Void has consumed much of the area.<br><br><br>\tSpawned from the depths of the Abyss, the Soulbinder is a vile and disgusting creature that prefers to consume its victims alive, devouring their souls during its digestion. It is the spirit of its prey that nourishes the beast, and this hunger is the only thing the beast knows. I know not how you will cause one of these monsters to shed a tear, but I believe you are resourceful enough to find a way.<br><br><br>\tJourney to the northeast, and follow the twisting strips of land surrounded by the Void; you should be able to locate a path to the lair of this foul thing. I wish I could provide you with guidance regarding approaching the beast, but I have been unable to discern anything beyond its location. Be on your guard, adventurer, and be prepared to do battle should the beast prove hostile.<br><br><br>",
	[1151131] = L"Ritual: Tears of a Soulbinder",
	[1005167] = L"inFaction",
	[1151129] = L"Have you met with Queen Oakwhisper?",
	[1151128] = L"Hail, adventurer.<br><br> I have heard of your continued assistance and loyalty to our Queen, and I cannot thank you enough for what you have done.  Our darkest hour is approaching, and you have truly proven a valuable ally. <br><br>The Queen and her Advisor have begun preparing the empowerment ritual with the previous components you gathered. They have made excellent progress and have informed me they are almost ready for the final two components.  Thus, I have been tasked with pointing you in the right direction.<br><br>\tFirst, they require a strand of hair from a dryad queen.<br><br>\tForces of nature unto themselves, dryad queens oversee the rule of the lush and verdant forests throughout our world.  You must seek out Oakwhisper, Queen of the Fire Island dryad clan. She has aided us in the past and we hope she shall be willing do so once again.<br><br>\tJourney to Fire Island and venture deep into the labyrinthine woods.  What you seek is an ancient, majestic tree that towers above all of the rest; it stands within a clearing full of life. <br><br> Hanging upon this tree is a magical standard; place your hand upon it and you will be transported to Queen Oakwhisper's bower.<br><br>Approach the Dryad Queen and ask for her assistance.",
