	[1074046] = L"Fur is Murder",
	[1074047] = L"Leather and Lace",
	[1074048] = L"Inventive Tools",
	[1074049] = L"Passage of Time",
	[1074050] = L"The Glass Eye",
	[1074051] = L"Artificial Life",
	[1074052] = L"Breeze's Song",
	[1074053] = L"Safety Helmet",
	[1074054] = L"The Shield",
	[1074055] = L"Instrument of War",
	[1074056] = L"Mightier than the Pen",
	[1074057] = L"Tipping the Dragon Scales",
	[1074058] = L"Fine Steels",
	[1074059] = L"Precious Metals",
	[1074060] = L"Leather Supplies",
	[1074061] = L"Quite the Yarn",
	[1074062] = L"Dead Man's Ingredients",
	[1074063] = L"Fine then, I shall find another to run my errands then.",
	[1074064] = L"Hurry up! I don't have all day to wait for you to bring what I desire!",
	[1074065] = L"These human made goods are laughable! It offends so -- I must show you what elven skill is capable of!",
	[1074066] = L"We elves are no strangers to archery but I would be interested in learning whether there is anything to learn from the human approach. I would gladly trade you something I have if you could teach me of the deadly crossbow bolt.  ",
	[1074067] = L"I wish to try a bow crafted in the human style. Is it possible for you to bring me such a weapon? I would be happy to return this favor.",
	[1074068] = L"I have heard of a curious type of bow, you call it a \"crossbow\". It sounds fascinating and I would very much like to examine one closely. Would you be able to obtain such an instrument for me?",
	[1074069] = L"These human \"crossbows\" are complex and clever. The \"heavy crossbow\" is a remarkable instrument of war. I am interested in seeing one up close, if you could arrange for one to make its way to my hands. ",
	[1074070] = L"My friend, I am in search of a device, a instrument of remarkable human ingenuity. It is a repeating crossbow. If you were to obtain such a device, I would gladly reveal to you some of the secrets of elven craftsmanship.",
	[1074071] = L"Humans artistry can be a remarkable thing. For instance, I have heard of a wonderful instrument which creates the most melodious of music. A lap harp. I would be ever so grateful if I could examine one in person. ",
	[1074072] = L"How clever humans are -- to understand the need of feet to rest from time to time!  Imagine creating a special stool just for weary toes.  I would like to examine and learn the secret of their making.  Would you bring me some foot stools to examine?",
	[1074073] = L"Humans have remarkable desire to secure what they \"possess\". I would be fascinated to see how a human would choose to contain something in a wooden chest. Do you think you could bring me such an item, in exchange for knowledge of elven ways?",
	[1074074] = L"The manner by which humans produce cloth is remarkable. A spinning wheel -- how clever! Could you arrange for me to experiement with such a device? ",
	[1074075] = L"I understand men decorate their living spaces with furniture such as a cherry armoire. It sounds like a beautiful, if strange invention. I would appreciate an opportunity to examine the craftsmanship on such an object.",
	[1074076] = L"Such a simple ingredient, yet so versatile! Sweet dough -- what can it not do? I would love to experiment and discover new frontier in the baking arts -- if only I had a supply of this sweet dough. ",
	[1074077] = L"I have heard tales of a potent dish. One that is both strong, yet delicate. Rich, but light. A baked quiche. Such culinary wizardry sounds delightful and I would be very appreciative to one who could provide me with such a meal.",
	[1074078] = L"I am told of a speciality dish, a meal of carefully prepared fish. Such a sushi platter must be sublime in its delicacy. I would be eternally grateful if you could provide me with such meal.",
	[1074079] = L"Humans have a splendid dish I am told, one that harvests the fruits of nature and tastes like drops of the golden sun! A peach cobbler. Such a dish must be priceless, but if you could provide it for me to taste, I would happily teach you more of the elven ways.",
	[1074080] = L"I desire to try a simple human meal. Something hearty, but simple. Perhaps, a cut of ribs? Yes, that sounds right. Perhaps, if you were to provide this for me, I could instruct you in the ways of elven cooking?",
	[1074081] = L"My friend, perhaps you are interested in elven wine? It is a wondrous elixir but I require a supply of that most precious fruit, a bunch of grapes. Please, bring some to me.<br>",
	[1074082] = L"I have discovered through great effort the dread after effects of human wine. My friend, I would be forever in your debt if you provide for me some of these cure potions which removes the efforts of noxious toxins. ",
	[1074083] = L"I understand men are not unfamiliar with the winemaking arts. Does the wine of humans quench thirst like the dew off a morning lily? Perhaps I could see for myself?",
	[1074084] = L"We elves are interested in trading our wines with humans but we understand human usually trade such brew in strange transparent bottles. If you could provide some of these empty glass bottles, I might engage in a bit of elven winemaking",
	[1074085] = L"Oh, the deviltry! Why would humans lock their precious liquors inside a wooden coffin? I understand I need a \"keg tap\" to access the golden brew within such a wooden abomination. Perhaps, if you could bring me such a tap, we could share a drink and I could teach you.",
	[1074086] = L"What wonders! A concotion that let's one see in the darkest night! How marvelous! Perhaps, you would obtain for me such night sight potions so that I might banish the darkest from my eyes. ",
	[1074087] = L"In a perilous world, one can never be too cautious. I understand mankind has developed a potion of healing to cure terrible injuries. I am certain we elves could benefit from this knowledge, so if you bring healing potions to me, I will teach you of elven lore.",
	[1074088] = L"These alchemy of humans is a wondrous and destructive art! I hear that an \"explosive\" potion produces a force of fiery potency when used. It sounds fascinating and I would like to see with my own eyes. Are you able to bring me such explosive potions?",
	[1074089] = L"The power of a great forrest fire contained in a simple glass container? How remarkable and terrible! I must see for myself. Could you bring for me some of these greater conflagration potions? I will, naturally, reciprocate the favor.",
	[1074090] = L"Human friend, tell me, is it true there is a dark side to the human art of alchemy? It is troubling to hear such tales -- I feel I must examine the toxins humans produce. Please, bring to me a supply of the deadliest poison humans craft. For this favor, I will grant you precious elven knowledge. ",
	[1074091] = L"Most human apparel is\x2026interesting to elven eyes. But there is one garment -- the flower garland -- which sounds very elven indeed. Could I see how a human crafts such an object of beauty? In exchange, I could share with you the wonders of elven garments.",
	[1074092] = L"I have heard noble tales of a fine and proud human garment. An article of clothing fit for both man and god alike. It is called a \"kilt\" I believe? Could you fetch for me some of these kilts so I that I might revel in their majesty and glory?",
	[1074093] = L"We elves believe that beauty is expressed in all things, including the garments we wear. I wish to understand more about human aesthetics, so please kind traveler -- could you bring to me magnificent examples of human fancy shirts? For my thanks, I could teach you more about the beauty of elven vestements.",
	[1074094] = L"Forgive me for saying this, but so much of human clothing is strange to elven eyes. For instance, the fur sarong. I have difficultry believing what I hear, so I must gaze upon it with my own two eyes. Bring some to me and I will happily repay the favor.",
	[1074095] = L"It is my understanding, the females of humankind actually wear on certain occasions a studded bustier? This is not simply a fanciful tale? Remarkable! It sounds hideously uncomfortable as well as ludicrously impractical. But perhaps, I simply do not understand the nuances of human clothing. Perhaps, I need to see such a studded bustier for myself?",
	[1074096] = L"What a thing, this human need to tinker. It seems there is no end to what might be produced with a set of Tinker's Tools. Who knows what an elf might build with some? Could you obtain some tinker's tools and bring them to me? In exchange, I offer you elven lore and knowledge. ",
	[1074097] = L"Elves find it remarkable the human preoccupation with the passage of time. To have built instruments to try and capture time -- it is a fascinating notion. I would like to see how a clock is put together. Maybe you could provide some clocks for my experimentation?",
	[1074098] = L"The wonders of human invention! Turning sand and metal into a far-seeing eye! This is something I must experience for myself. Bring me some of these spyglasses friend human",
	[1074099] = L"Is it true human? There are those among your kind who can construct an autonomaton that mocks the shape of a man? It is a frightening but intriguing notion! I must see these golems for myself. Please, bring me a golem and I will reward you with an elven teaching. ",
	[1074100] = L"To give voice to the passing wind, this is an idea worthy of an elf! Friend, bring me some of the amazing fancy wind chimes so that I may listen to the song of the passing breeze. Do this, and I will share with you treasured elven secrets.",
	[1074101] = L"I am curious to see the results of human blacksmithing. To examine the care and quality of a simple item. Perhaps, a simple bascinet helmet? Yes, indeed -- if you could bring to me some bascinet helmets, I would demonstrate my gratitude. ",
	[1074102] = L"The clank of human iron and steel is strange to elven ears. For instance, the metallic heater shield which human warriors carry into battle. It is odd to an elf, but nevertheless intriguing. Tell me friend, could you bring me such an example of human smithing skill?",
	[1074103] = L"What would you say is a typical human instrument of war? Is a broadsword a typical example? I wish to see more of such human weapons, so I would gladly trade elven knowledge for human steel. ",
	[1074104] = L"There is supposedly a terrible and impressive blade forged by the hand of man. The no-dachi, a sword which requires great smithy skills. I would be honored to view the work of such a mastery human smith. If you can assist me, I would be greatly honored. ",
	[1074105] = L"Mankind, I am told, knows how to take the scales of a terrible dragon and forge them into powerful armor. Such a feat of craftsmanship! I would give anything to view such a creation -- I would even teach some of the prized secrets of the elven people. ",
	[1074106] = L"Is there a finer metal than valorite? I hear tell of its wonders, but I confess I do not believe the half of it. I must see for myself. Kind human, bring me a supply of this valorite so that I might examine it more closely. ",
	[1074107] = L"They say men greatly covet metal colored like the fair Sosarian sun. These golden ingot with their mystical properties are of great interest to the elven people. I would be greatly indebted to a human who brough me a supply of golden ingots. ",
	[1074108] = L"Where does one get some of this horned leather, my friend? What are its properties? How difficult is it to work? Ah, perhaps these questions would be more easily answered if you simply brought me some of this horned leather. What do you say human?",
	[1074109] = L"I cannot help myself human. I see these balls of yarn and I wish to bat them around as if they were prey to be hunted. Please, human, bring me more of these strange and delightful balls of joys. Bring me more yarn!",
	[1074110] = L"Well, where are the cotton bales?",
	[1074111] = L"I have heard of a strange breed of magic, one that draws its power from the forces of death. This is not the elven way, but I confess my curiosity to understand more. Could you gather for me a quantity of the grave dust used in this necromantic magic?",
	[1074112] = L"What do humans know of archery? Humans can barely shoot straight. Why, your efforts are absurd. In fact, I will make a wager -- if these so called human arrows I've heard about are really as effective and innovative as human braggarts would have me believe, then I'll trade you something useful.  I might even teach you something of elven craftsmanship.",
	[1074113] = L"Human craftsmanship! Ha! Why, take an elven bow. It will last for a lifetime, never break and always shoot an arrow straight and true. Can't say the same for a human, can you? Bring me some of these human made bows, and I will show you.",
	[1074114] = L"Leave it to a human to try and improve upon perfection. To take a bow and turn it into a mechanical contraption like a crossbow. I wish to see more of this sort of \"invention\". Fetch for me a crossbow, human.",
	[1074115] = L"How lazy is man! You cannot even be bothered to pull your own drawstring and hold an arrow ready? You must invent a device to do it for you? I cannot understand, but perhaps if I examine a heavy crossbow for myself, I will see their appeal. Go and bring me such a device and I will repay your meager favor.",
	[1074116] = L"More is always better for a human, eh? Take these repeating crossbows. What sort of mind invents such a thing? I must look at it more closely. Bring such a contraption to me and you'll receive a token for your efforts.",
	[1074117] = L"You think you know something of music? Laughable! Take your lap harp. Crude, indelicate instruments that make a noise not unlike the wailing of a choleric child or a dying cat. I will show you -- bring lap harps, and I will demonstrate.",
	[1074118] = L"Human fancy knows no bounds!  It's pathetic that they are so weak that they must create a special stool upon which to rest their feet when they recline!  Humans don't have any clue how to live.  Bring me some of these foot stools to examine and I may teach you something worthwhile.",
	[1074119] = L"You would lock away all your possessions, fearing thieves everywhere, wouldn't you human? It is folly to put things in your wooden chests, flimsy as they are. I will show you how inferior they are to elven craftsmanship.",
	[1074120] = L"Thread should woven by delicate touch, not so elaborate machine as a spinning wheel. Still, there is something intriguing about the human approach. Bring some spinning wheels, so I might see how inferior thread is created.",
	[1074121] = L"If an elf were to create a piece of furniture, you know it would be a thing of magnificent beauty! I will show you -- bring to me a cherry armoire, what some humans would call a \"beautiful\" thing. Bring this, and I will point out all the ways in which it is flawed.",
	[1074122] = L"I have tasted human breads and I find them pathetic and lacking. Perhaps, it is the ingredients? Bring for me some of this sweet dough so that I might see how you humans go wrong. Do this and I might show you how real food is created.",
	[1074123] = L"I wish that humans could cook something at least half-way palatable to an elf. But alas, it is all gruel. Though these baked quiches sound promising. I expect they're awful, but you never know. Perhaps, you could bring some for me to try?",
	[1074124] = L"I daresay, a human would eat dirt and straw if it were served on a plate. Raw fish and weeds of the ocean? To eat a sushi platter -- what madness! I can scarcely believe it. You must bring for me a sample of such fare, so that I may see for myself. ",
	[1074125] = L"I am told human-made peach cobbler is a dish worthy of an elf's palate. This, I very much doubt. In fact, I will prove it. Fetch for me some of these peach cobblers and then I will show you a truly magnificent dish!",
	[1074126] = L"You hack the ribcage off of some beast and then eat it? And call that a meal? Absurd! I will not believe it until you bring me an example of these cuts of ribs, so I might see it for myself.",
	[1074127] = L"Humans take perfectly wonderful grapes and reduce them to the laundry water you call wine! I will show you real elven wine. Bring to me bunches of grapes, so you might know what true craftsmen can achieve.",
	[1074128] = L"I have sampled human vintage and it has made me deathy ill. I require a cure for such poison. Bring me some cure potions, so I might recover from what humans call \"wine\".",
	[1074129] = L"Do not think it ego when I say elves are superior in all ways. For example, bring a bottle of your wine so that I might gag it down. If you compare it to wonderful elven vintage and you will understand.",
	[1074130] = L"The only good thing I can say about human made bottles is that they are empty and may yet still be filled with elven wine. Go now, fetch a number of empty bottles so that I might save them from the fate of carrying human-made wine.",
	[1074131] = L"I have acquired a barrel of human brewed beer. I am loathe to drink it, but how else to prove how inferior it is? I suppose I shall need a barrel tap to drink. Go, bring me a barrel tap quickly, so I might get this over with.",
	[1074132] = L"Why do humans want to see in the dark? Lurking in shadows to spy on others, that sounds like a human to me! Well, elves can fight fire with fire. Bring me some of these night sight potions and we will even the score.",
	[1074133] = L"Humans are so clumsy and stupid, always hurting themselves. I suppose that's why they have healing potions. Hmmm, I wonder what goes into such a concotion? Go and fetch me a sample, so I might investigate.",
	[1074134] = L"If humans are going to have explosive potions, we elves must learn more about how they are brewed. I demand you bring some of these bottles of destruction to me right away!",
	[1074135] = L"The mindless destruction humans cause! They really brew potions of greater conflagration! I must see for myself -- bring me some directly, and I will reward you.",
	[1074136] = L"I knew humans were treacherous devils. Take the deadly poisons they brew! To be used against who, I wonder? Bring me deadly poison potions, so I might have proof of human's murderous ways.",
	[1074137] = L"Humans do not deserve to wear a thing such as a flower garland. Help me prevent such things from falling into the clumsy hands of humans -- bring me flower garlands!",
	[1074138] = L"I do not believe humans are so ridiculous as to wear something called a \"kilt\". Bring for me some of these kilts, if they truly exist, and I will offer you meager reward.",
	[1074139] = L"Humans call that a fancy shirt? I would wager the ends are frayed, the collar worn, the buttons loosely stitched. Bring me fancy shirts and I will demonstrate the many ways in which they are inferior.",
	[1074140] = L"To murder creatures of the forrest for such a ridiculous garment as a fur sarong! It boggles the mind. Perhaps, the skins of the poor animals can be made into a proper garment. Bring me fur sarongs, so I might bring some dignity to the dead creatures.",
	[1074141] = L"No self respecting elf female would ever wear a studded bustier! I will prove it -- bring me such clothing and I will show you how ridiculous they are!",
	[1074142] = L"Bring me some of these tinker's tools! I am certain, in the hands of an elf, they will fashion objects of ingenuity and delight that will shame all human invention! Hurry, do this quickly and I might deign to show you my skill.",
	[1074143] = L"Elves find it remarkable the human preoccupation with the passage of time. To have built instruments to try and capture time -- it is a fascinating notion. I would like to see how a clock is put together. Maybe you could provide some clocks for my experimentation?",
	[1074144] = L"Humans are so pathetically weak, they must be augmented by glass and metal! Imagine such a thing! I must see one of these spyglasses for myself, to understand the pathetic limits of human sight!",
	[1074145] = L"Imagine! A mechanical thing which mocks a man! A golem, what an idea. I am curious about how humans create such a monstrous thing. Perhaps, I can learn more to use it against the devious humans. Go, get me a golem so I might see it more closely. ",
	[1074146] = L"I understand humans cruely enslave the very wind to their selfish whims! Fancy wind chimes, what a monstrous idea! You must bring me proof of this terrible depredation -- hurry, bring me wind chimes!",
	[1074147] = L"You want to discuss the pathetic qualities of human craftsmanship? How about their bascinet helmets -- weak and flimsy things, your head would be better protect by maple leaves or a bit of straw. I will show you -- bring me some bascinet helmets and I will show you how pathetic they are.",
	[1074148] = L"I doubt very much a human shield would stop a good stout elven arrow. You doubt me? I will show you -- get me some of these heater shields and I will piece them with sharp elven arrows!",
	[1074149] = L"Pathetic, this human craftsmanship! Take their broadswords -- overgrown butter knives, in reality. No, I cannot do them justice -- you must see for yourself. Bring me broadswords and I will demonstrate their feebleness. ",
	[1074150] = L"Some humans think their no-dachis are impressive swords. I'd rather fight with an elven quill pen in hand! I will show you how clumsy and dull they are if you bring me a few, so that we might mock their inferior workmanship.",
	[1074151] = L"Forging a great suit of armor from the scales of a dragon seems an idea worthy of an elf -- so I'm sure these humans have ruined it. Bring me a complete suit of this dragon armor, so I might see all the ways in which humans have done an inferior job of creation.",
	[1074152] = L"Well, where are the boards?",
	[1074153] = L"Valorite is one of the few metals that seems worthy of an elf's attention. With such a metal, I could craft something that would demonstrate the pinnacle of elven superiority! Get me some valorite ingots so I might forge such an item!",
	[1074154] = L"Humans lust so terribly for gold. Pathetic really. They barely understand what can be done with the metal. I will demonstrate what elves can craft if you'll bring some of the golden ingots. ",
	[1074155] = L"I require a quantity of horned leather to craft something that will inspire awe, wonder and fear among the sad humans. Hurry, fetch for me this horned leather so that I might shame human craftsmen everywhere!",
	[1074156] = L"Here's a task even a human could do. Bring me balls of yarn. Yes, balls of yarn. Even pathetically made human yarn will do, for in the hands of an elf, wonders can be achieved. ",
	[1074157] = L"Humans will violate the graves of their own kind? Truly? I would have thought human indencency had some boundaries, but apparently, I am wrong. Prove this is true -- bring to me some human gathered grave dust.",
	[1074158] = L"Ah good, you're back.  We're eager for the feast.",
	[1074159] = L"As you open the iron maiden, your surroundings mysteriously change!",
	[1074160] = L"I will take the ears you have collected now.  Hand them here.",
	[1074161] = L"Access to Bedlam by invitation only",
	[1074162] = L"You notice a hole in the tree and climb down",
	[1074163] = L"You find a way to climb back outside the tree",
	[1074164] = L"An insane dryad comes out of a nearby tree and attacks you!",
	[1074165] = L"You feel dizzy from a lack of clear air",
	[1074166] = L"Have you gathered the mushrooms?",
	[1074167] = L"Well done!  Well done, indeed.  You are worthy to become an arcanist!",
	[1074168] = L"Seeker's Symbol",
	[1074169] = L"Suit yourself human.",
	[1074170] = L"I will not aid you human, unless you renounce your humanity.",
	[1074171] = L"Ahloestree, friend.",
	[1074172] = L"Certainly.  There is plenty of time to explore such things.  Return to me should you decide the time is now.",
	[1074173] = L"Ah Seeker, I had not thought to see you again in that form.  Perhaps you have difficulty finding the wise Darius?  I do not know where he wanders, but I can tell you that he is always curious, so perhaps you'll find him near a great curiousity?",
	[1074174] = L"*sniff* fish! much-fish!",
	[1074175] = L"Thiiirsty. Hurrr. Hurrr.",
	[1074176] = L"Ah, thus it ends.",
	[1074177] = L"*giggle* So pretty!",
	[1074178] = L"Sap of Sosaria",
	[1074179] = L"Well enough done.  It's best to kill quickly with respect so there isn't suffering.",
	[1074180] = L"Do you have them?  Let me see.",
	[1074181] = L"Has it been done?",
	[1074182] = L"Did you find it?",
	[1074183] = L"You there! I have a job for you.",
	[1074184] = L"Come here, I have work for you.",
	[1074185] = L"Hey you! Want to help me out?",
	[1074186] = L"Come here, I have a task.",
	[1074187] = L"Want a job?",
	[1074188] = L"Weakling! You are not up to the task I have.",
	[1074189] = L"Hey tough guy! I have a job, but I doubt you are up too it. \x00a0It requires someone far braver then you.",
	[1074190] = L"*sigh* Oh no. You won\x2019t do at all.\x00a0 Look at you, so weak, so puny.\x00a0 Oh no no no. ",
	[1074191] = L"Just keep walking away!\x00a0 I thought so. Coward!\x00a0 I\x2019ll bite your legs off! ",
	[1028616] = L"palisade",
	[1074193] = L"You there! Yes you. Stop looking about like a toadie and come here.",
	[1028617] = L"wooden wall",
	[1074195] = L"You there, in the stupid hat!   Come here.",
	[1028618] = L"wooden wall",
	[1074197] = L"Pardon me, but if you could spare some time I\x2019d greatly appreciate it.",
	[1028619] = L"wooden wall",
	[1074199] = L"Help! I need somebody! Won\x2019t you please, please help me!",
	[1028620] = L"wooden wall",
	[1074201] = L"Waste not a minute! There\x2019s work to be done. ",
	[1028621] = L"wooden wall",
	[1074203] = L"Hello friend. I realize you are busy but if you would be willing to render me a service I can assure you that you will be judiciously renumerated.",
	[1028622] = L"wooden wall",
	[1074205] = L"Oh great adventurer, would you please assist a weak soul in need of aid?",
	[1028623] = L"wooden wall",
	[1074207] = L"Good day to you friend! Allow me to offer you a fabulous opportunity!\x00a0 Thrills and adventure await! ",
	[1028624] = L"wooden wall",
	[1074209] = L"Hey, could you help me out with something? ",
	[1028625] = L"log wall",
	[1074211] = L"I could use some help.",
	[1028626] = L"log wall",
	[1074213] = L"Hey buddy.\x00a0 Looking for work?",
	[1028627] = L"log wall",
	[1074215] = L"Don\x2019t test my patience you sniveling worm!",
	[1028628] = L"log wall",
	[1074217] = L"I want to make you an offer you\x2019d be a fool to \x00a0refuse. ",
	[1028629] = L"log wall",
	[1074219] = L"Hello there, can I have a moment of your time?",
	[1028630] = L"log wall",
	[1074221] = L"Greetings!\x00a0 I have a small task for you good traveler. ",
	[1028631] = L"log wall",
	[1074223] = L"Have you done it yet?\x00a0 Oh, I haven\x2019t told you, have I?",
	[1028632] = L"log wall",
	[1074225] = L"A noble deed you have done this day.  This reward is nothing to a hero such as yourself.",
	[1074226] = L"You have not disappointed me.  Enjoy your reward.",
	[1074227] = L"I am pleased to hear that you have abided by my wishes in this delicate matter.  Here is your recompense.",
	[1074228] = L"someone's dagger",
	[1074229] = L"Coil's Fang",
	[1074230] = L"Thrasher's Tail",
	[1074231] = L"Abscess' Tail",
	[1028636] = L"nodraw",
	[1074233] = L"Tainted Seeds",
	[1028637] = L"log wall",
	[1074235] = L"Unknown",
	[1028638] = L"log wall",
	[1074237] = L"Starving",
	[1028639] = L"log wall",
	[1074239] = L"Overfed",
	[1028640] = L"log wall",
	[1074241] = L"Unknown",
	[1074242] = L"Dead",
	[1074243] = L"Dying",
	[1074244] = L"Unhealthy",
	[1074245] = L"Healthy",
	[1074246] = L"Strong",
	[1074247] = L"Live Creatures: ~1_NUM~ / ~2_MAX~",
