	[1028815] = L"wraith form",
	[1074591] = L"Fandancer Fish",
	[1028816] = L"exorcism",
	[1074593] = L"Jellyfish",
	[1074594] = L"Stripped Sosarian Swill",
	[1074595] = L"Stripped Flake Fish",
	[1074596] = L"Shrimp",
	[1074597] = L"A Full Moon Fish  ",
	[1074598] = L"A shell",
	[1074599] = L"A shell",
	[1074600] = L"An island statue",
	[1074601] = L"Fish bones",
	[1074602] = L"An unusual creature has hatched overnight in the tank.",
	[1074603] = L"You rub the slimy ointment on your body, temporarily protecting yourself from the corrosive river.",
	[1074604] = L"The slimy ointment continues to protect you from the corrosive river.",
	[1074605] = L"You're not getting a refund without the proper forms and signatures.",
	[1074606] = L"If you're not willing to follow the proper process then go away.",
	[1074607] = L"Oh blast!  Not another of those forms.  I'm so sick of this endless paperwork.",
	[1074608] = L"You Scratch My Back",
	[1074609] = L"Heh.  Heheheh.  Good one.  You're not a Bedlam student and you're definitely not eligible for a tuition refund.  Heheheh. That old witch Aernya doesn't see as well as she used to you know.  Otherwise, she would have ... hmmm, wait a minute.  I sense a certain 'opportunity' here.  I'll sign your forms in return for a little help with a project of my own.  What do you say?",
	[1074610] = L"Tuition Reimbursement Form (in triplicate)",
	[1074611] = L"Unicorn Ribs",
	[1028826] = L"scroll of calling",
	[1074613] = L"Pixie Leg",
	[1028827] = L"Scroll of Abraxus",
	[1074615] = L"Hehehe.  Your choice.",
	[1028828] = L"cleanse by fire",
	[1074617] = L"Oh excellent, you're back.  I'll get the oven going.  That thing about pixie legs, you see, is that they burn and dry out if you're not really careful.  Taste just like chicken too!",
	[1028829] = L"close wounds",
	[1074619] = L"Now that I've signed your papers you'd better get back to that witch Aernya.  Mmmm mmm smell those ribs!",
	[1028830] = L"consecrate weapon",
	[1074621] = L"You better hurry back to Mistress Aernya with that signed form.  The college only has so much money and with enough claims you may find yourself unable to get your tuition refunded.  *wink*",
	[1028831] = L"dispel evil",
	[1074623] = L"Not Quite That Easy",
	[1028832] = L"divine fury",
	[1074625] = L"Completed Tuition Reimbursement Form",
	[1028833] = L"enemy of one",
	[1074627] = L"What are you waiting for?  The iron maiden is still the portal to Bedlam.",
	[1028834] = L"holy light",
	[1074629] = L"Convince Me",
	[1028835] = L"noble sacrifice",
	[1074631] = L"No signature for you.",
	[1028836] = L"remove curse",
	[1074633] = L"Pulled it off huh?  Well then you've earned this signature!",
	[1028837] = L"sacred journey",
	[1074635] = L"Well, there you are.  I've added my signature to that of Gorrow, so you should be set to return to Mistress Aernya and get your tuition refunded.",
	[1028838] = L"Armor Ignore",
	[1074637] = L"Just head out the main gates there and you'll find yourself embracing the iron maiden in the Bloodletter's Guild.",
	[1028839] = L"Bleed Attack",
	[1074639] = L"Orders from Minax",
	[1028840] = L"Concussion Blow",
	[1074641] = L"I've heard ... there's some that will pay a good bounty for pointed ears, much like we used to pay for each wolf skin.  I've got nothing personal against these elves.  It's just business.  You want in on this?  I'm not fussy who I work with.",
	[1028841] = L"Crushing Blow",
	[1074643] = L"I can't pay a bounty if you don't bring bag the ears.",
	[1028842] = L"Disarm",
	[1074645] = L"Dreadhorn",
	[1028843] = L"Dismount",
	[1074647] = L"How can you not feel as I do?",
	[1028844] = L"Double Strike",
	[1074649] = L"Thank you.  I haven't the words to express my gratitude.",
	[1028845] = L"Infecting",
	[1074651] = L"Or, you could keep the journal for your private library.",
	[1028846] = L"Mortal Strike",
	[1074653] = L"Shhhh!  What have YOU done to that book?  It's covered in ... is that blood?  *furious glare*  Let me see that.  Oh.  Oh, I see.  Do you realize how important this journal is?  Here, take this for your trouble.",
	[1028847] = L"Moving Shot",
	[1074655] = L"Perhaps I thought too highly of you.",
	[1028848] = L"Paralyzing Blow",
	[1074657] = L"I am overjoyed with your efforts!  Your devotion to Sosaria is noted and appreciated.",
	[1028849] = L"Shadow Strike",
	[1074659] = L"*wailing cries* Then begone if you will not help a poor man in need.",
	[1028850] = L"Whirlwind Attack",
	[1074661] = L"You've found it?  My lucky dagger!",
	[1028851] = L"Riding Swipe",
	[1074663] = L"*nods*",
	[1028852] = L"Frenzied Whirlwind",
	[1074665] = L"I can't be generous, my friend, until you bring me those crystalline fragments.",
	[1028853] = L"Block",
	[1074667] = L"My friend, you've returned -- with items for me, I hope?  I have a generous reward for you.",
	[1028854] = L"Defense Mastery",
	[1074669] = L"Good, you're here.  The presence of a twisted creature deep under the earth near Nu'Jelm has corrupted the natural growth of crystals in that region.  They've become infused with the twisting energy -- they've come to a sort of life.  This is an abomination that festers within Sosaria.  You must eradicate the crystal lattice seekers.",
	[1028855] = L"Nerve Strike",
	[1074671] = L"These abominations must not be permitted to fester!",
	[1028856] = L"Talon Strike",
	[1074673] = L"You have done well.  Enjoy this reward.",
	[1028857] = L"Feint",
	[1074675] = L"Primitive Fetish",
	[1028858] = L"Dual Wield",
	[1074677] = L"I've always been fascinated by primitive cultures -- especially the artifacts.  I'm a collector, you see.  I'm working on building my troglodyte display and I'm saddened to say that I'm short on examples of religion and superstition amongst the creatures.  If you come across any primitive fetishes, I'd be happy to trade you something interesting for them.",
	[1028859] = L"Double Shot",
	[1074679] = L"Bravo!  These fetishes are just what I needed.  You've earned this reward.",
	[1028860] = L"Armor Pierce",
	[1074681] = L"A Trog and His Dog",
	[1028861] = L"Bladeweave",
	[1074683] = L"Not half bad.  Here's your prize.",
	[1028862] = L"Force Arrow",
	[1074685] = L"I have created a masterpiece!  And all I need to finish it off is the fur of a bear.  But not just ANY bear -- oh no, no, that wouldn't do.  I've heard tales of a mighty beast, Grobu, who is bonded to the leader of the troglodytes.  Only Grobu's fur will do.  Will you retrieve it for me? ",
	[1028863] = L"Lightning Arrow",
	[1074687] = L"Ah! So soft, so supple.  What a wonderful texture.  Here you are ... my thanks.",
	[1028864] = L"Psychic Attack",
	[1074689] = L"Oh nevermind, you don't look capable of my task afterall.  Haha!  What was I thinking -- you could never handle killing troglodytes.  It'd be suicide.  What?  I don't know, I don't want to be responsible ... well okay if you're really sure?",
	[1028865] = L"Serpent Arrow",
	[1074691] = L"You still need to kill those troglodytes, remember?",
	[1028866] = L"Force of Nature",
	[1074693] = L"Vile creatures have exited the sinkhole and begun terrorizing the surrounding area.  The demons are bad enough, but the elementals are an abomination, their poisons seeping into the fertile ground here.  Will you enter the sinkhole and put a stop to their depredations?",
	[1074694] = L"The daemons that have congregated to worship Paroxysmus pose a tremendous danger. Will you enter the lair and see to their destruction?",
	[1074695] = L"The moloch daemons that have congregated to worship Paroxysmus pose a tremendous danger. Will you enter the lair and see to their destruction?<br>",
	[1074696] = L"The succubi that have congregated within the sinkhole to worship Paroxysmus pose a tremendous danger. Will you enter the lair and see to their destruction?<br>",
	[1074697] = L"The arcane daemons that worship Paroxysmus pose a tremendous danger. Will you enter the lair and see to their destruction?<br>",
	[1074698] = L"You have discovered an acid covered strongbox.  Perhaps the owner would pay for its return before the corrosive substance destroys it.  Do you wish to return the box?",
	[1074699] = L"The box doesn't look like it will survive the acid for much longer anyway.",
	[1074700] = L"The steaming box is etched with the name of Aeluva.",
	[1074701] = L"The disintegrating strongbox belonged to Jelrice.",
	[1074702] = L"The acid damaged coffer is etched with the name 'Belulah'.",
	[1074703] = L"Hello.  Oh, what's that?  My trunk!  What happened to it?  Well nevermind that.  Thank you!  Here's payment for your trouble.",
	[1074704] = L"Please, please I beg of you ... help out of here.  I was trying to find one of my sheep that went missing and I fell down this hole.  Then these ... *hysterical weeping*.  Please, get me out of here!",
	[1074705] = L"Please!  PLEASE!  Don't let me die here.",
	[1074706] = L"*whimper* Please ... hurry.  I am a good climber and could get out the way you came in, if you can just get me there.",
	[1074707] = L"You've saved my life!  Oh thank you!  I can't repay you for your kindness but please, take this.",
	[1074708] = L"A Bad Seed",
	[1074709] = L"The plight of the forest is staggering, all the more so because some of the tainted creatures are reproducing.  I am working to develop a natural means to prevent these corrupted seedlings from taking root, but without samples of such seeds, I'm forced to guess wildly what might work.  Will you harvest some tainted bogling seeds for me?",
	[1074710] = L"I'm working on a striking necklace -- something really unique -- and I know just what I need to finish it up.  A huge fang!  Won't that catch the eye?  I would like to employ you to find me such an item, perhaps a snake would make the ideal donor.  I'll make it worth your while, of course.",
	[1074711] = L"Scale Armor",
	[1074712] = L"Here's what I need ... there are some creatures called hydra, fearsome beasts, whose scales are especially suitable for a new sort of armor that I'm developing.  I need a few such pieces and then some supple alligator skin for the backing.  I'm going to need a really large piece that's shaped just right ... the tail I think would do nicely.  I appreciate your help.",
	[1074713] = L"The Medallion",
	[1074714] = L"You have discovered an insciption on the back of the medallion that reads 'love always, your Belulah'.  Since the wearer of the necklace has met a grisly end, perhaps you'd be willing to track down Belulah?",
	[1074715] = L"You are already protected with this slimy ointment.",
	[1074716] = L"You are no longer under the protection of the slimy ointment.",
	[1074717] = L"Certain tamed animals are accepted as donations by transfering the pet to the collection box.",
	[1074718] = L"Tainted seeds please.  Look for the bigggest, meanest bogling you can find.",
	[1074719] = L"<CENTER>Food Decoration Tool</CENTER>",
	[1074720] = L"This is perfect!",
	[1074721] = L"Do you have it?  *gasp* What a tooth!  Here \x2026 I must get right to work.",
	[1074722] = L"Those really big snakes like swamps, I've heard.  You might try the blighted grove.",
	[1074723] = L"I understand.  I don't like snakes much either.  They're so creepy.",
	[1074724] = L"Hydras have been spotted in the Blighted Grove.  You won't get those scales without getting your feet wet, I'm afraid.",
	[1074725] = L"I can't wait to get to work now that you've returned with my scales.",
	[1074726] = L"A Tale of Tail",
	[1074727] = L"I've heard of you, adventurer.  Your reputation is impressive, and now I'll put it to the test. This is not something I ask lightly, for this task is fraught with danger, but it is vital.  Seek out the vile hydra Abscess, slay it, and return to me with its tail.",
	[1074728] = L"Well, the beast will still be there when you are ready I suppose.",
	[1074729] = L"Em, I thought I had explained already.  Abscess, the hydra, you know? Lots of heads but just the one tail.  I need the tail. I have my reasons. Go go go.",
	[1074730] = L"Ah, the tail.  You did it!  You know the rumours about dried ground hydra tail powder are all true?  Thank you so much!",
	[1074731] = L"Or you could keep the medallion instead.",
	[1074732] = L"The name 'Belulah' is the only clue you find on the medallion.",
	[1074733] = L"Greets!  How can I \x2026 oh.  Oh no!  Is that \x2026 my darling Thorvald!  *quiet weeping*  Thank you for your kindness in returning this to me.  It means \x2026 a lot.  *sniffle*",
	[1074734] = L"The hero returns from the glorious battle and - oh, such a small feather?",
	[1074735] = L"If you're going to get anywhere in the adventuring game, you have to take some risks.  A harpy, well, it's bad, but it's not a dragon.",
	[1074736] = L"The path to greatness isn't for everyone obviously.",
	[1074737] = L"I've seen how you strut about, as if you were something special. I have some news for you, you don't impress me at all. It's not enough to have a fancy hat you know.  That may impress people in the big city, but not here. If you want a reputation you have to climb a mountain, slay some great beast, and then write about it.  Trust me, it's a long process.  The first step is doing a great feat.  If I were you, I'd go pluck a feather from the harpy Saliva, that would give you a good start.",
	[1074738] = L"A Feather in Yer Cap",
	[1074739] = L"Guile, Irk and Spite",
	[1074740] = L"You know them, don't you.  The three?  They look like you, you'll see. They looked like me, I remember, they looked like, well, you'll see.  The three.  They'll drive you mad too, if you let them.  They are trouble, and they need to be slain.  Seek them out.",
	[1074741] = L"Drool",
	[1074742] = L"When I was a child I was savaged by a Cu'Sidhe.  It ran up and slobbered all over me. Long story short:  it was horrible, I was traumatized and I've never been the same since.  Look at me now.  Kill them, kill them all.  Well at least a few.",
	[1074743] = L"I don't think I'm asking anything unreasonable here.",
	[1074744] = L"Slaughter me some  -- Cu'Sidhe.  I'm a poet!",
	[1074745] = L"You just don't understand the gravity of the situation.  If you did, you'd agree to my task.",
	[1074746] = L"Perhaps I was unclear.  You'll know them when you see them, because you'll see you, and you, and you.  Hurry now.",
	[1074747] = L"Are you one of THEM?  Ahhhh!  Oh, wait, if you were them, then you'd be me.  So you're -- you.  Good job!",
	[1074748] = L"It's rare to find someone who shares my aversions and is willing to take immediate measures.  I'm glad we met.",
	[1074749] = L"Ha ha!  This just goes to prove that there's no request that someone is not willing to fuffilll.  Well done my friend!",
	[1074750] = L"Momento!",
	[1074751] = L"I was going to march right out there and get it myself, but no ... Master Gnosos won't let me.  But you see, that bridle means so much to me.  A momento of happier, less-dead ... well undead horseback riding.  Could you fetch it for me?  I think my horse, formerly known as 'Resolve', may still be wearing it.",
	[1074752] = L"Hrmph.",
	[1074753] = L"The bridle would be hard to miss on him now ... since he's skeletal.  Please do what you need to do to retreive it for me.",
	[1074754] = L"I'd know that jingling sound anywhere!  You have recovered my bridle.  Thank you.",
	[1074755] = L"Culinary Crisis",
	[1074756] = L"You have NO idea how impossible this is.  Simply intolerable!  How can one expect an artiste' like me to create masterpieces of culinary delight without the best, fresh ingredients?  Ever since this whositwhatsit started this uproar, my thrice-daily produce deliveries have ended.  I can't survive another hour without produce!",
	[1074757] = L"You have no artistry in your soul.",
	[1074758] = L"I must have fresh produce and cheese at once!",
	[1074759] = L"Those dates look bruised!  Oh no, and you fetched a soft cheese.  *deep pained sigh*  Well, even I can only do so much with inferior ingredients.  BAM!",
	[1074760] = L"A hydra scale",
	[1074761] = L"Resolve's Bridle",
	[1028901] = L"Runebook",
	[1150275] = L"wheat wort",
