	[1076389] = L"\"Then he felt with his paws just in back of his ears\"",
	[1076390] = L"\"And he suddenly realized the worst of his fears.\"",
	[1076391] = L"\"'I'm ruined,' he shouted, oh what'll I do! I'd rather be dead or go live in a zoo!'\"",
	[1076392] = L"\"'And if anyone sees me, oh what a disgrace, So I'd better discover a good hiding place!'\"",
	[1076393] = L"Oh, but I told it just a bit ago... mayhaps later?",
	[1076394] = L"'Tis very spacious! It containeth the royal throne, a commemorative shield, and the Serpent Crest.",
	[1076395] = L"Many a day and eve my lord sat there upon... *teehee* Yet it hath such an odd shape!",
	[1076396] = L"Oh yes, not like those from Magincia or Nujel'm 'tall!",
	[1076397] = L"The red one over on yonder wall. It hath a wonderful inscription, but I do not know who Govannon Mac Lyr was",
	[1076398] = L"May Truth Be My Sword, Courage My Shield, And Love Guide Them Both. It speaketh well of the Three Principles",
	[1076399] = L"The silver serpent stands boldly 'pon the red field, a symbol of strength for all!",
	[1029720] = L"Adranath",
	[1076401] = L"I hath but seen one once, yet now know why my liege feeleth so strongly of their power and dignity",
	[1029721] = L"Lord Blackthorn",
	[1076403] = L"'Twas once reserved for only the finest of horses for the Royal Guard, yet now anyone canst purchase a steed therein",
	[1029722] = L"Captain Dasha",
	[1076405] = L"*teehee* Sometimes I sneak through the walls to fetch a quick snack. The guards sometimes leave out rations",
	[1029723] = L"Dawn",
	[1076407] = L"Most of these nobles visit from far away places, like Magincia or Moonglow. Some are very friendly!",
	[1029724] = L"Warlord Kabur",
	[1076409] = L"I eat there every day, I highly recommend the brie!",
	[1076410] = L"The nobles get odd looks upon their faces if I go there during meals... so I eat in the kitchen",
	[1076411] = L"'Tis a wonderful library full of rare books and histories. A pity I am so small, or I would read more!",
	[1076412] = L"Lord British once slept in that very room! It also hath a secret!",
	[1076413] = L"Uh-huh! And we would read stories before bedtime, 'twas wonderful! I sleep on a pillow near the bed",
	[1076414] = L"The good Commander leant it to me, 'twas most kind!",
	[1076415] = L"If thou examineth the north wall most carefully, ye should find the entrance to milord's study!",
	[1076416] = L"Oh, but please be careful therein, the castle staff oft forget to clean it methinks",
	[1076417] = L"Many of the land's finest artists come here to paint portraits",
	[1076418] = L"Be veryyy careful in there! Nystul used to make things explode all the time! Clainin is no better!",
	[1076419] = L"I asked Clainin what happened to him... but no one seemeth to have a good answer for me",
	[1029730] = L"Solen queen",
	[1076421] = L"'Tis so big! I used to sit in 'pon many a meeting between Lord British and his Council",
	[1029731] = L"Solen warrior",
	[1076423] = L"The Commander gave me a fluffy pillow!",
	[1029732] = L"Solen worker",
	[1076425] = L"This isn't the first castle, of course! 'Tis built upon the remains of older castles as the kingdom grew",
	[1029733] = L"arcane demon",
	[1076427] = L"Yes, quite a few are intertwined with the castle's sewer, but people are too big to fit!",
	[1029734] = L"betrayer",
	[1076429] = L"Well, wouldst thou like to know more about the grounds or the inside?",
	[1029735] = L"bogling",
	[1076431] = L"'Tis behind the castle's southwest wing. There was a time when it bustled with activity!",
	[1029736] = L"bog thing",
	[1076433] = L"Oh, there's the throne room, dining hall, kitchen, meeting hall, studio, laboratory, library, and my lord's bedroom",
	[1029737] = L"chaos demon",
	[1076435] = L"I know not where, but I shall wait for him!",
	[1029738] = L"chariot",
	[1076437] = L"Oh, well, 'tis been a hard time for Britannia, yet the Council seemeth able to stay the course",
	[1029739] = L"Exodus minion",
	[1076439] = L"Our proud country's borders extend across the waves! E'en be it Trammel or Felucca, many call it home",
	[1029740] = L"Exodus Overseer",
	[1076441] = L"Our homeland, from which many fled as Minax's armies laid waste to the kingdom...",
	[1029741] = L"doppleganger",
	[1076443] = L"May his name be cursed for ever and ever, 'tis his fault that so many troubles were wrought upon my lord",
	[1029742] = L"Moloch demon",
	[1076445] = L"I canst not even comprehend that strange and horrible being",
	[1029743] = L"giant beetle",
	[1076447] = L"Yes! My lord read me many a story from a strange and wonderful land called... 'Urth?' I think 'twas.",
	[1029744] = L"golem",
	[1076449] = L"Wouldst thou like to hear the story?",
	[1029745] = L"horde demon",
	[1076451] = L"That's a silly way to pronounce it!",
	[1029746] = L"juggernaut",
	[1076453] = L"The world which we know was once Sosaria, but now is one kingdom",
	[1029747] = L"plague beast",
	[1076455] = L"After the Stranger defeated Mondain, my lord bound together the shattered remnants of our world into one kingdom",
	[1029748] = L"quagmire",
	[1076457] = L"Hast thou read, 'My Story?' It recordeth many a strange thing about our world",
	[1029749] = L"ridgeback",
	[1076459] = L"Akalabeth and the Lands of the Lost King became the Lands of Lord British, and the capital of Akalabeth became Britain",
	[1029750] = L"sand vortex",
	[1076461] = L"Truth, Love and Courage - from which flow all the Eight Virtues",
	[1029751] = L"skeletal mount",
	[1076463] = L"Amo!",
	[1029752] = L"sphinx",
	[1076465] = L"Oh! So few know the mantra of the Axiom of Infinity! How wonderful!",
	[1029753] = L"swamp dragon",
	[1076467] = L"Aye, 'tis represented in this very castle!",
	[1029754] = L"swarm",
	[1076469] = L"Ahm!",
	[1029755] = L"plague beast",
	[1076471] = L"Ra!",
	[1029756] = L"Meer mage",
	[1076473] = L"Cah!",
	[1029757] = L"Meer warrior",
	[1076475] = L"Om!",
	[1029758] = L"Juka mage",
	[1076477] = L"I'm Sherry!",
	[1029759] = L"Juka warrior",
	[1076479] = L"Oh! You said it right!",
	[1076480] = L"Hehe, I write books, eat cheese, and talk to people",
	[1076481] = L"I love cheese! Dost thou have any?",
	[1076482] = L"Some people think 'tis an odd thing, but I'm even trying to learn new languages!",
	[1076483] = L"Aye! One day I wish to be able to talk to every intelligent race in the world",
	[1076484] = L"Oh, for some time I hath been traveling, seeking answers",
	[1076485] = L"I canst not tell thee more, for I am sworn to secrecy",
	[1076486] = L"Aye! I am a mouse!",
	[1076487] = L"... I'm sorry to see what happened to him",
	[1076488] = L"I... I canst not tell thee of that",
	[1076489] = L"*Squeak*",
	[1076490] = L"*Squeek*",
	[1076491] = L"*Squirk*",
	[1076492] = L"*Squeak, squirk?*",
	[1076493] = L"*Squeeeeeek!*",
	[1076494] = L"*Eeeek!*",
	[1076495] = L"*Nitters fiblik*",
	[1076496] = L"Ne'er have I seen such a grim game as the one played that eve. For every move there was found a counter!",
	[1076497] = L"A pawn for a pawn, a knight for a knight, and then the field was left with naught but lonely kings.",
	[1076498] = L"And alone, neither could overturn the other...",
	[1076499] = L"The very air was torn asunder, as though the air had been peeled away. Beyond it lay darkness and stars",
	[1076500] = L"T'were not unlike the night sky, yet deeper and more ethereal",
	[1076501] = L"I never wish to feel such a thing again!",
	[1076502] = L"The Time Lord's voice penetrated me to the core. Didst he know I was there, that I and Blackthorn both witnessed this?",
	[1076503] = L"I know something of the nature of worlds, yet in what kind of place canst one such as the Time Lord dwell?",
	[1076504] = L"Lord British told me of it, how such an artifact of evil could be created I darest not imagine.",
	[1076505] = L"Thou knowest then, that our world is but a shadow of another Britannia.",
	[1076506] = L"Perhaps it is the wrong word? Yet we are not the true Britannia, and for this my lord is gone...",
	[1076507] = L"I... understand the price that would have been paid. Yet they tell me my lord found another way",
	[1076508] = L"Long after Blackthorn's death, though. Oh how such a horrible fate could be visited on such a noble man!",
	[1076509] = L"All life that was unique to our world, gone! Erased as though it had never existed?",
	[1076510] = L"I pray the protections that shield our own shard remain strong",
	[1076511] = L"No ill fate awaits our world now should the people embrace the virtues. Yet, they do not!",
	[1076512] = L"He seemeth to be an entity from beyond our own dimension, tasked with watching the multiverse",
	[1076513] = L"Our world is not alone, for there are thousands upon thousands reflections of the original Britannia",
	[1076514] = L"After the Gem was shattered, each shard kept a likeness of the world within it. Such was its power!",
	[1076515] = L"Yes, yet, save that night in Lord British's chambers, I hath not seen him. Perhaps he is somehow limited?",
	[1076516] = L"Nystul once spoke of a barrier surrounding our shard, as though it blocked outside interferences",
	[1076517] = L"Perhaps the barrier canst be breached?",
	[1076518] = L"Oh! Excuse me, I must be going",
	[1076519] = L"Sorry! I have to be going",
	[1076520] = L"It's breakfast time!",
	[1076521] = L"I'm off for Lunch!",
	[1076522] = L"Dinnertime!",
	[1076523] = L"I'm getting a little sleepy... good night!",
	[1076524] = L"Our finest soldiers are trained here and at Serpent's Hold",
