	[1078623] = L"Anatomy allows you to evaluate the ability of other creatures and improves healing.  At 60 you can cure poison in yourself and others.  At 75 you can see your enemy's fatigue as a percentage.  At 80 you can use a bandage to resurrect a ghost.",
	[1078624] = L"- Click the Icon in the Skills Window<BR>- Target a nearby animal, monster, pet, or player",
	[1078625] = L"- Increases combat damage",
	[1078626] = L"Playguide/Skills: Anatomy<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_1.php",
	[1078627] = L"   Animal Lore is a skill in which you are able to determine the health, needs, and special functions of an animal.",
	[1078628] = L"- Click the Icon in the Skills Window<BR>- Target a nearby animal, monster, or pet",
	[1078629] = L"- Partially determines your ability to control a pet<BR>- Influences success of the Veterinary skill",
	[1078630] = L"Playguide/Skills: Animal Lore<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_2.php",
	[1078631] = L"   Animal Taming will allow you to tame an animal to which you will then be able to give simple commands. This animal will remain with you so long as you keep it well fed and happy. In order to determine the state of your pet, you might wish to learn Animal Lore.",
	[1078632] = L"- Click the Icon in the Skills Window<BR>- Target a nearby, untamed animal or monster<BR>- Stay close to your target while your attempt at taming progresses",
	[1078633] = L"Playguide/Skills: Animal Taming<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_35.php",
	[1078634] = L"   Archery is a combat skill in which the combatant uses the bow as the primary weapon. Archery is unique in that it requires arrows. If you have a bow equipped, you can attack a player, animal, NPC or monster as you normally would. The bow / crossbow will fire so long as you have arrows / bolts in your backpack. You can attack your target so long as you have direct line of sight to them.",
	[1078635] = L"* A bow or crossbow<BR>* Arrows or bolts",
	[1078636] = L"- Equip a bow or crossbow<BR>- Enter combat mode<BR>- Target a living creature",
	[1078637] = L"Playguide/Skills: Archery<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_31.php",
	[1078638] = L"   Arms Lore is the ability to determine strengths and weaknesses in weapons or armor. It can even be used to perceive the nature of Swamp Dragon armor, or the quality of a Golem. A knowledge of Arms Lore also benefits crafters, who can create items with extra properties.",
	[1078639] = L"- Click the Icon in the Skills Window<BR>- Target a weapon, piece of armor, Swamp Dragon, or a Golem",
	[1078640] = L"- Bonus to Damage Increase on weapons when exceptionally crafted<BR>- Bonus to resists on armor when exceptionally crafted",
	[1078641] = L"Playguide/Skills: Arms Lore<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_4.php",
	[1078642] = L"   Begging is the ability for you to receive alms from NPCs. When you desperately need gold, you can beg for it. You will lose karma, but you might gain a few coins.",
	[1078643] = L"- Click the Icon in the Skills Window<BR>- Target a nearby NPC",
	[1078644] = L"Playguide/Skills: Begging<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_6.php",
	[1078645] = L"   To use your Blacksmithing skill, you will need to be near an anvil and forge. When standing near these you may use your tools to repair items, melt items, or craft items. A menu will appear once you use a blacksmithing tool near the anvil and forge.",
	[1078646] = L"* A Smith's hammer, sledge hammer, or tongs<BR>* Ingots<BR>* A nearby anvil and forge",
	[1078647] = L"- Double-click a Smith's hammer, sledge hammer, or tongs<BR>- Choose an item to craft from the menu",
	[1078648] = L"Playguide/Skills: Blacksmithing<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_7.php",
	[1078649] = L"   Bushido is the main skill of the Samurai, and embodies the very essence of honorable combat. With it, and the Book of Bushido, the Samurai can perform a variety of special abilities that are defensive in nature, but can be used to quickly and honorably defeat the toughest of opponents.",
	[1078650] = L"* Book of Bushido",
	[1078651] = L"- Open the Book of Bushido<BR>- Click the Icon of the ability you wish to use",
	[1078652] = L"Playguide/Skills: Bushido<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_52.php",
	[1078653] = L"   When you're far away from a safe night's sleep, be it home or inn or even just a guarded area, there's a natural way to quickly log out.",
	[1078654] = L"* A bedroll<BR>* Kindling",
	[1078655] = L"- Place the kindling on the ground<BR>- Double-click the kindling to ignite it, this may take several tries<BR>- Wait until you receive confirmation that the campsite is secure<BR>- Place the bedroll on the ground<BR>- Double-click the bedroll to unroll it<BR>- Double-click the bedroll to log out safely",
	[1078656] = L"Playguide/Skills: Camping<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_10.php",
	[1078657] = L"   The carpenter is able to fashion useful items from wood such as furniture, musical instruments, and even additions to homes. A carpenter uses tools such as saws, nails, and joining planes when creating items.",
	[1078658] = L"* A carpentry tool, such as a saw<BR>* Boards or logs",
	[1078659] = L"- Double-click the carpentry tool<BR>- Choose an item to craft from the menu",
	[1078660] = L"Playguide/Skills: Carpentry<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_11.php",
	[1078661] = L"   The Cartography skill has two primary uses. It can be used to create one of several types of maps. Secondly, it is used to decode treasure maps that are sometimes found as loot on monsters.",
	[1078662] = L"* Mapmaker's Pen<BR>* Blank Map",
	[1078663] = L"* Creating a map<BR>  - Double-click the Mapmaker's Pen<BR>  - Choose the type of map you wish to create<BR>* Decoding a treasure map<BR>  - Double-click the treasure map; success depends on your skill level",
	[1078664] = L"Playguide/Skills: Cartography<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_12.php",
	[1078665] = L"   Chivalry is the main ability of the Paladin. With it, and the Book of Chivalry, a Paladin can evoke a number of abilities that can improve his prowess on the battlefield.<BR><BR>   Each ability a Paladin wishes to invoke will require a certain amount of \"tithing points\" to use. A Paladin can earn these tithing points by donating gold at a shrine or holy place. And while he is free to be generous and tithe as much as he likes, there will be a limit as to how many points a Paladin can have at any one time.",
	[1078666] = L"* Book of Chivalry",
	[1078667] = L"- Open the Book of Chivalry<BR>- Click the Icon of the ability you wish to use",
	[1078668] = L"Playguide/Skills: Chivalry<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_51.php",
	[1078669] = L"   Cooking allows you to bake raw food into tastier cooked food. First you must locate or build a fire, and have something to cook with. The Cooking skill also allows you to try to combine certain foods to make new dishes.",
	[1078670] = L"* A heat source<BR>* A cooking utensil<BR>* Raw food or ingredients",
	[1078671] = L"- Locate or build a fire<BR>- Double-click a cooking utensil<BR>- Choose the meal you wish to create from the menu",
	[1078672] = L"Playguide/Skills: Cooking<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_13.php",
	[1078673] = L"   Detect Hidden is useful skill in several regards. Proficiency in this skill will allow you to detect hidden players, find traps on trapped chests, and detect dungeon traps. The higher your level of proficiency with this skill, the larger your search radius will be, and the greater chance you have of detecting other sorts of traps.",
	[1078674] = L"- Click the Icon in the Skills window<BR>- Target the area you wish to search",
	[1078675] = L"Playguide/Skills: Detecting Hidden<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_14.php",
	[1078676] = L"   Music may soothe the savage beast, but playing a few clashing notes will weaken even the strongest of creatures.",
	[1078677] = L"* A musical instrument",
	[1078678] = L"- Click the Icon in the Skills Window<BR>- Target a nearby animal or monster",
	[1078679] = L"Playguide/Skills: Discordance<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_15.php",
	[1078680] = L"Evaluating intelligence allows you to learn certain things about the mental makeup of the beings you select. If you need to know how intelligent a being is and get an idea of their potential magic using ability, you will need to learn evaluate intelligence. A high evaluate intelligence skill also allows mages to successfully overcome the natural resistance of creatures to magic. Therefore, a high evaluate intelligence skill may make a huge difference to a mage.",
	[1078681] = L"- Click the Icon in the Skills Window<BR>- Target a nearby living creature",
	[1078682] = L"- Bonus to spell damage",
	[1078683] = L"Playguide/Skills: Evaluating Intelligence<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_16.php",
	[1078684] = L"The art of fencing requires a dexterous hand, a quick wit and fleet feet. ",
	[1078685] = L"* A fencing weapon",
	[1078686] = L"- Equip a fencing weapon<BR>- Enter combat mode<BR>- Target a living creature",
	[1078687] = L"Playguide/Skills: Fencing<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_42.php",
	[1078688] = L"   The art of bowcraft and fletching allows bowyers to rely on the forests of Britannia for their weaponry. One who truly lives off the land, a bowyer may carve his bows, crossbows, arrows and bolts from the very trees around him, thus avoiding the need to ever venture to town.",
	[1078689] = L"* Fletcher's tools<BR>* Feathers<BR>* Logs or boards",
	[1078690] = L"- Double-click the fletching tool<BR>- Choose the item you wish to create from the menu",
	[1078691] = L"Playguide/Skills: Fletching<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_8.php",
	[1078692] = L"   Use of the fishing skill will allow you to catch fish from large bodies of water. Double-click on a fishing pole, then click on a body of water. If successful, you will catch a fish. Success with this skill also depends on the availability of fish in that specific area. You can also catch other items, including treasure maps and SOS messages in bottles.",
	[1078693] = L"* A fishing pole",
	[1078694] = L"- Equip a fishing pole while near a body of water<BR>- Double-click the fishing pole<BR>- Target the location in the water where you wish to fish",
	[1078695] = L"Playguide/Skills: Fishing<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_18.php",
	[1078696] = L"   The Focus skill could be defined as the \"Warrior's Meditation Skill.\" It increases both a player's Mana and Stamina regeneration. Since a warrior's swing rate is determined by the amount of stamina he has, the ability to increase the regeneration of that attribute would be highly beneficial on the battlefield. Mana, too, is an important stat to any warrior that uses special combat moves as part of his tactics.",
	[1078697] = L"- Regenerates Stamina and Mana over time",
	[1078698] = L"Playguide/Skills: Focus<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_50.php",
	[1078699] = L"   Use of this skill will allow you to find information about a corpse, and the events surrounding its demise. The higher your skill level, the higher your chances of determining these events, and the accuracy of your description.",
	[1078700] = L"- Click the Icon in the Skills Window<BR>- Target a corpse, player, or container",
	[1078701] = L"Playguide/Skills: Forensic Evaluation<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_19.php",
	[1078702] = L"   Use of the healing skill will allow you to heal yourself or other players. If you are successful in your efforts, the recipient will regain health, and the bandage will be used up. To create bandages, simply use scissors on cloth.",
	[1078703] = L"- Double-click on a bandage<BR>- Target the person you wish to heal",
	[1078704] = L"Playguide/Skills: Healing Skill<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_17.php",
	[1078705] = L"   Use of this skill will allow you to herd animals. The higher your skill, the more likely you are to successfully herd the animal.",
	[1078706] = L"* A shepherd's crook",
	[1078707] = L"- Equip a shepherd's crook<BR>- Double-click the crook<BR>- Target the animal you wish to herd<BR>- Target the location you wish the animal to move toward",
	[1078708] = L"Playguide/Skills: Herding<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_20.php",
	[1078709] = L"   The hiding skill allows you to become invisible to other players. You will be revealed if you move, speak, cast a spell, loot a body, attack someone or something, and other possible ways. It can be very difficult or impossible to hide while you are being attacked, so make sure to run a good distance away from your enemy and exit combat mode before attempting to hide. While you are hidden, you are not totally impervious to detection or attack. You can be revealed by spellcasters, the Detect Hidden skill, and can be tracked using the tracking skill. You can also take damage from area effect spells, and purple potions. You must remain wary even while hidden.",
	[1078710] = L"- Click the Icon in the Skills Window",
	[1078711] = L"Playguide/Skills: Hiding<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_21.php",
	[1078712] = L"   Inscribed in a steady hand and imbued with the power of reagents, a scroll can mean the difference between life and death in a perilous situation. Those knowledgeable in Inscription may transcribe spells to create useful magical scrolls.",
	[1078713] = L"* Two books: a source and a blank to copy into<BR>* Scribe's pen, a spellbook, associated reagents, and a blank scroll",
	[1078714] = L"- Click the Icon in the Skills Window<BR>- Target the book you wish to copy<BR>- Target the blank book to copy into",
	[1078715] = L"- Double-click the Scribe's pen<BR>- Select the spell you wish to copy from your spellbook",
	[1078716] = L"- Bonus to certain spells' damage",
	[1078717] = L"Playguide/Skills: Inscription<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_23.php",
	[1078718] = L"   Item Identification will allow you to discern the relative value of an item to NPCs.",
	[1078719] = L"- Click the Icon in the Skills Window<BR>- Target the item you wish to identify",
	[1078720] = L"Playguide/Skills: Item Identification<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_3.php",
	[1078721] = L"   The lockpicking skill is exactly that, it is used to open locked items. In order to attempt to pick a lock, you must have a set of lockpicks in your pack. Lockpicks can be purchased from thief shopkeepers. Some locks are harder to pick than others (and some, such as house doors, are impossible to pick). Your skill level will determine your success rate. If you are successful the lock will be picked, and you can open the item.",
	[1078722] = L"* A lockpick",
	[1078723] = L"- Double-click the lockpick<BR>- Target the item you wish to pick",
	[1078724] = L"Playguide/Skills: Lockpicking<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_24.php",
	[1078725] = L"   The use of the lumberjacking skill will allow you to gain raw materials in the form of logs. The logs can then be used for carpentry, bowyering, or tinkering. If you are successful in recovering wood it will be placed in your pack.",
	[1078726] = L"* An axe, hatchet, or polearm",
	[1078727] = L"- Equip the axe, hatchet, or polearm<BR>- Double-click the axe, hatchet, polearm<BR>- Target a tree",
	[1078728] = L"- Bonus to weapon damage when using an axe type weapon",
	[1078729] = L"Playguide/Skills: Lumberjacking<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_44.php",
	[1078730] = L"   Mace fighting is a melee combat skill, which allows for an quick attack style of fighting. A mace fighter is capable of using a War Axe, Club, Hammer Pick, Mace, Magic Wand, Maul, Smithy Hammer, War Hammer, War Mace, Black Staff, Gnarled Staff, Quarterstaff, and Shepherd's Crook in combat to great effect.",
	[1078731] = L"* A mace type weapon",
	[1078732] = L"- Equip the mace type weapon<BR>- Enter combat mode<BR>- Target a living creature",
	[1078733] = L"Playguide/Skills: Mace Fighting<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_41.php",
	[1078734] = L"   This skill will allow you to cast a variety of spells in the game. The magery skill is automatically checked when you attempt to cast a spell, and your skill level will determine your chances of success in the attempt. To cast a spell, your hands must be free of any items (except a spellbook), you must have a spellbook with the appropriate spell contained therein, and you must have the appropriate reagents in your pack.<BR>   It is also possible to cast a spell from a scroll. The proper reagents and skill are necessary to prepare the scroll initially, so casting from a scroll requires no reagents, and can be done with a lower level of skill.",
	[1078735] = L"* A magery spellbook<BR>* Reagents<BR>* Or: A spell scroll",
	[1078736] = L"- Open the Book of Magery<BR>- Click the Icon of the ability you wish to use<BR>- Or: Double-click the spell scroll you wish to use",
	[1078737] = L"Playguide/Skills: Magery<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_25.php",
	[1078738] = L"   Mana, the powerful substance used in casting spells from scrolls or spellbooks, as well as in the practice of inscription, is as rich as gold to any who use its power on a daily basis. The Meditation skill allows spellcasters and others to increase the rate at which they regenerate Mana.",
	[1078739] = L"- Click the Icon in the Skills Window",
	[1078740] = L"- Restores Mana over time",
	[1078741] = L"Playguide/Skills: Meditation<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_46.php",
	[1078742] = L"   While the name of this skill may suggest that it helps with resisting all spells, this is not the case. This skill helps you lessen the severity of spells that lower your stats or ones that last for a specific duration of time. It does not prevent direct-damage spells, like Energy Bolt or Flamestrike.",
	[1078743] = L"- Lessens impact of certain stat-changing and duration based spells<BR>- Bonus to minimum elemental resists at 40+ skill",
	[1078744] = L"Playguide/Skills: Resisting Spells<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_26.php",
	[1078745] = L"   Cultivating the mining skill enables you to harvest the seams of ore that lie in the mines and mountains of Britannia. This ore can then be smelted into ingots (using the mining skill) and the ingots can then be used to craft various items, such as armor (using the blacksmithing skill).",
	[1078746] = L"* A pickaxe or shovel",
	[1078747] = L"* Mining<BR>  - Double-click the pickaxe or shovel<BR>  - Target the mountainside or cave wall<BR>* Smelting<BR>  - Stand near a forge<BR>  - Double-click a pile of ore in your backpack",
	[1078748] = L"Playguide/Skills: Mining<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_45.php",
	[1078749] = L"   Use of the musicianship skill will allow you to play an instrument. The ability to play an instrument is necessary for some other skills such as discordance, provocation, and peacemaking. A music sample will play if you succeed, but an ugly noise will occur if you fail. The higher your skill level, the greater your chances of playing a pretty tune.",
	[1078750] = L"* A musical instrument",
	[1078751] = L"- Double-click the musical instrument",
	[1078752] = L"Playguide/Skills: Musicianship<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_29.php",
	[1078753] = L"   Necromancy is the study of dark magic. With it, and a special book called the Tome of Necromancy, you can curse your foes, animate the dead, transform into wicked creatures, and summon some of the most deadly spells in the world.",
	[1078754] = L"* A Tome of Necromancy<BR>* Necromancy Reagents",
	[1078755] = L"- Open the Tome of Necromancy<BR>- Click the Icon of the ability you wish to use",
	[1078756] = L"Playguide/Skills: Necromancy<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_49.php",
	[1078757] = L"   Ninjitsu is the main skill of the Ninja, and combines the arts of stealth, espionage and assassination. With it, and the book of Ninjitsu, a Ninja can evoke a number of special abilities including transforming into a variety of creatures that give unique bonuses, using stealth to attack unsuspecting opponents or just plain disappear into thin air!",
	[1030899] = L"soulstone",
	[1078759] = L"- Open the Book of Ninjitsu<BR>- Click the Icon of the ability you wish to use",
	[1030900] = L"soulstone",
	[1078761] = L"   This skill is used to determine your proficiency at blocking attacks with a shield. If you are using a shield, this skill is checked automatically each time that you are attacked. If successful, your attacker may miss his attack, or do less damage than normal.",
	[1030901] = L"soulstone",
	[1078763] = L"- Equip a shield in your off hand, Parrying will reduce damage during combat",
	[1030902] = L"soulstone",
	[1078765] = L"   Use of the peacemaking skill will allow you to stop all fights in your immediate area. This skill is related to your musicianship skill, and will automatically check this skill when you use peacemaking. ",
	[1030903] = L"<center>Soulstone</center>",
	[1078767] = L"- Click the Icon in the Skills Window<BR>* Single Creature<BR><BR>  - Target a nearby animal, monster, or pet<BR>* Area Peacemaking<BR>  - Target yourself",
	[1078768] = L"Playguide/Skills: Peacemaking<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_9.php",
	[1078769] = L"   The Poisoning skill can be used to poison a weapon or even food and drink. This will cause damage to whoever is attacked with the poisoned weapon, or to whoever consumes the food or drink. To poison a weapon simply use the skill from your skill list, and then select the vial of poison you wish to use, and finally click on the item you wish to poison. If you poison a weapon, you will lose karma. This item will now be poisoned until you use it. Once the poisoned weapon is used you will have to repeat the process to poison it again.<BR><BR>When you wish to poison an item, DO NOT double click the green potion first. If you do this, you will drink the poison. This does not give you the results you had hoped for, as you will have just poisoned yourself.",
	[1078770] = L"* A poison potion",
	[1078771] = L"- Click the Icon in the Skills Window<BR>- Target the poison potion<BR>- Target the weapon, food, or drink you wish to poison",
	[1078772] = L"- Influences strength of the Poison spell",
	[1078773] = L"Playguide/Skills: Poisoning<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_30.php",
	[1078774] = L"   This skill is used to encourage other creatures to fight one other. You will need a musical instrument to accomplish this task. If you are successful the two creatures will fight for a time consistent with their respective natures and dispositions. Please keep in mind that you cannot provoke other characters.",
	[1078775] = L"* A musical instrument",
	[1078776] = L"- Click the Icon in the Skills Window<BR>- Target a nearby animal, monster, or pet",
	[1078777] = L"Playguide/Skills: Provocation<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_22.php",
	[1078778] = L"   The skilled rogue will be able to disarm traps using the Remove Trap skill. In order to begin learning the art of removing traps you must first demonstrate proficiency at Lockpicking, and Detect Hidden. You must have a base level of 50 skill in both of those skills before you can begin your training in this area.",
	[1078779] = L"- Click the Icon in the Skills Window<BR>- Target a trapped container",
	[1030910] = L"statue",
	[1078781] = L"   The Snooping skill is used to see into another player's backpack. Be warned however that a large majority of players do not care for a player who frequents the use of this skill. This skill is best used in conjunction with stealing.",
	[1030911] = L"statue",
	[1078783] = L"Playguide/Skills: Snooping<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_28.php",
	[1030912] = L"statue",
	[1078785] = L"* A Spellweaving book<BR>* An arcane focus",
	[1078786] = L"- Open the Spellweaving book<BR>- Click the Icon of the ability you wish to use",
	[1078787] = L"Playguide/Skills: Spellweaving<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_54.php",
	[1078788] = L"   Spirit Speak is used to be able to understand the speech of ghosts. If you do not have this skill you will only be able to see a series of \"OoOOoo\"s emanating from the deceased. The Spirit Speak skill is also used to heal players by channeling spiritual energy. Spiritual energy can be channeled from either a corpse or the player using the skill. If a corpse is not available, then the player will channel their own energy from their Mana.",
	[1078789] = L"- Click the Icon in the Skills Window<BR>- Target a nearby corpse",
	[1078790] = L"- Grandmasters can see hidden ghosts<BR>- Grandmasters can speak as a ghost and be understood by the living<BR>- Grandmasters can understand the speech of ghosts",
	[1078791] = L"Playguide/Skills: Spirit Speak<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_32.php",
	[1078792] = L"   The skilled Pickpocket may be able to steal items in several manners, from a variety of sources. You may be able to steal from monsters, chests, NPC's, or other players (if you are a member of the thieves guild, or if they are an opponent in a guild war).",
	[1078793] = L"* Random Pickpocketing<BR>  - Click the Icon in the Skills Window<BR>  - Target a container, creature, NPC, or player while standing nearby<BR>* Selective Pickpocketing<BR>  - Open a container with the Snooping skill<BR>  - Click the Icon in the Skills Window<BR>  - Target the item you wish to steal while standing nearby",
	[1078794] = L"Playguide/Skills: Stealing<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_33.php",
	[1078795] = L"   The person skilled in the ways of Stealth may learn to hide their movements and move invisibly.",
	[1078796] = L"- Click the Icon in the Skills Window for Hiding<BR>- Click the Icon in the Skills Window for Stealth",
	[1078797] = L"Playguide/Skills: Stealth<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_48.php",
	[1078798] = L"   Swordsmanship is a melee combat skill, which allows for a strong-arm attack style of fighting. A swordsperson is capable of using an axe, a battle axe, a double axe, an executioner's axe, a hatchet, a large battle axe, a pickaxe, a two-handed axe, a butcher knife, a cleaver, a skinning knife, a bardiche, a halberd, a broad sword, a cutlass, a katana, a longsword, a scimitar, or a viking sword in combat to slice there opponents to ribbons.",
	[1078799] = L"* A sword type weapon",
	[1078800] = L"- Equip a sword type weapon<BR>- Enter combat mode<BR>- Target a living creature",
	[1078801] = L"Playguide/Skills: Swordsmanship<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_40.php",
	[1078802] = L"   Tactical skill is the common sense of the fighting adventurer. A high skill in Tactics increases your proficiency with any type of weapon, allowing you to deal more damage in combat. ",
	[1078803] = L"- Increases combat damage",
	[1078804] = L"Playguide/Skills: Tactics<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_27.php",
	[1078805] = L"- Influences the success of several Ninjitsu abilities",
	[1078806] = L"   Use of the tailoring skill will allow you to make a wide variety of items, ranging from bandages to clothing, and even leather armor. Your raw materials can come from a variety of sources, from hunting animals for leather, to gathering cotton and spinning thread. You can also purchase materials from a vendor and craft them into items for resale.",
	[1078807] = L"* A sewing kit<BR>* Cloth or leather",
	[1078808] = L"- Double-click the sewing kit<BR>- Choose the item you wish to sew from the menu",
	[1078809] = L"Playguide/Skills: Tailoring<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_34.php",
	[1078810] = L"   Use of Taste Identification will allow you to determine the sort of potion you have in your possession, or to determine if an object is poisoned or not.",
	[1078811] = L"- Click the Icon in the Skills Window<BR>- Target the food, drink, potion, or potion keg you wish to taste",
	[1078812] = L"Playguide/Skills: Taste Identification<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_36.php",
	[1078813] = L"   The tinkering skill is used to make tools for other professions, and also to make clocks, sextants, and to trap containers. With this skill you can make hammers, tongs, scissors, smoothing planes, and numerous other tools. To make these tools and assorted items you will need a set of tinker's tools.",
	[1078814] = L"* Tinker's tools<BR>* Ingots or lumber",
	[1078815] = L"- Double-click the tinker's tools<BR>- Choose an item you wish to create from the menu",
	[1078816] = L"Playguide/Skills: Tinkering<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_37.php",
	[1078817] = L"   The tracking skill will allow you to track animals, monsters, and people. If you are successful, and an appropriate creature can be tracked, you will be told in what direction that creature can be found. The higher your skill level in tracking, the more likely you are to successfully track an object, and the farther you will be able to track it.",
	[1078818] = L"- Click the Icon in the Skills Window<BR>- Choose an animal, monster, or player from the menu",
	[1078819] = L"Playguide/Skills: Tracking<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_38.php",
	[1078820] = L"   The veterinary skill will allow you to heal animals in much the same way that the healing skill works on people. The amount of healing that you provide will be based on your skill level.",
	[1078821] = L"* Bandages",
	[1078822] = L"- Double-click on the bandage<BR>- Target the animal you wish to heal",
	[1078823] = L"Playguide/Skills: Veterinary<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_39.php",
	[1078824] = L"   This skill is used while in hand-to-hand combat (no weapon equipped). It is checked automatically when you fight, and may determine the frequency, and damage level with which you will strike your opponent.",
	[1078825] = L"- Unequip any weapon you're holding<BR>- Enter combat mode<BR>- Target a living creature",
	[1078826] = L"Playguide/Skills: Wrestling<BR>http://www.uoherald.com/guide/skill_43.php",
