	[1112577] = L"A swarm of snakes springs forth from the nest and attacks you!!!",
	[1150169] = L"<h2>The Royal City</h2><br>Capital of Ter Mur<br><br>The gargoyles are an ancient race with an advanced culture.  Their skill with architecture, especially stone, is second to none.  They have their own virtues, their own magic and have brought the skill of imbuing to the humans and elves of Britannia.  This is their capital city.<br><br>In spite of all their accomplishments, their world is dying.  The void has claimed all but the center of it, and this part remains only by the magic of the gargoyle queen, Zhah.<br><br>The gargoyles are naturally reclusive, but they have reached out to the humans for help as most of their natural resources have been lost to the void.<br><br>The Royal City is opulent and beautiful.  All manner of shops and traders can be found here.  It is the shining remnant of an empire that was.  Unless the gargoyles can find a way to push back the void and reclaim their land, it may claim them all and the world of the gargoyles will simply vanish.",
	[1150168] = L"<h2>New Haven</h2><br>The city of mystery<br><br>(This town is a great place to start as a new player)<br><br>Blackrock has plagued the kingdom of Britannia for all of recorded history.  It is a great temptress in that it contains incredible magical power.  No city in the kingdom is a better example of this than Haven.<br><br>Not so many years ago, Haven was a thriving and prosperous city.  Then one day mysterious blackrock traders came seeking large quantities of the cursed rock.  Adventurers from all over the kingdom brought blackrock to Haven to trade with these strangers.  Before anyone could discern their intent, the city became plagued with undead and its citizens vanished.<br><br>It is not known if the undead that haunt this place are the former villagers or if they are their ancestors, nor is it known if the undead plague is connected to the blackrock traders.<br><br>What is known is that \"New Haven\" sprung up almost overnight.  The citizens of New Haven claim to be time travelers who brought the new city with them through time.  Many do not believe this story.  Others think these strange folk may have caused the destruction of \"Old\" Haven. The citizens of New Haven have declined to explain further, claiming that doing so would \"disrupt the timeline.\"<br><br>Whatever the past may be, the present is a town that rivals the original Haven in prosperity and trade.",
