	[1112911] = L"As you gently hold the shard it begins to glow - the stars shining within seem to sing to the beautiful world turning softly below. A vision overwhelms you of tranquil cities where all races, be they men, elves, orc or gargoyle, have overcome their natural selves and founded a civilization built upon harmony and peace. For a moment, one pure moment, you feel every joyous life within, and cry out for the beauty of it all...",
	[1032179] = L"cave drawings",
	[1149637] = L"PRIME",
	[1032180] = L"cave drawings",
	[1149636] = L"Not Loaded",
	[1032181] = L"cave drawings",
	[1149635] = L"LOAD",
	[1032182] = L"cave drawings",
	[1112913] = L"The shard seems to draw your eye inwards as you gaze upon the world within. The stars above seem to shine coldly; the cloud below seem grey and heavy. Without bidding a vision enters your mind of the people living upon the tired world below: a people struggling to survive, to earn their daily bread by labor or by the sword. Little time is left for love and laughter, let alone the Virtues that might have united such a desperate band of men. You see nations at war and entire kingdoms crumbling with the sands of time...",
	[1032183] = L"cave drawings",
	[1149633] = L"flame cannonball",
	[1032184] = L"cave drawings",
	[1149632] = L"Not Charged",
	[1032185] = L"cave drawings",
	[1149631] = L"Charged",
	[1032186] = L"cave drawings",
	[1112915] = L"The shard cuts your hand and warm, wet blood seeps along its edges, obscuring the view within in a haze of crimson. A vision assaults you without warning, of war and death and terror. This world did not die for lack of Virtue, or the apathy of its inhabitants - no, this world was ripped asunder by the very forces of darkness that threaten your own. With this realization comes a feeling of joy; the feeling of chaos and destruction overwhelms you, and you see that even you can inflict such a fate on your own world if you wish...",
	[1032187] = L"cave drawings",
	[1149629] = L"REMOVE",
	[1032188] = L"cave drawings",
