	[1075570] = L"A simple, hand crafted gift box. ***NOT BLESSED***",
	[502078] = L"You do not have enough dexterity to equip this item",
	[1075568] = L"Bring warmth and light to your home",
	[1075566] = L"A comfortable addition to any room",
	[1075564] = L"Bringing small daily gifts of reagents",
	[502079] = L"The instrument played its last tune.",
	[1075562] = L"An antique house placement tool",
	[1075560] = L"Just a moment my friend, just a moment! *rummages in his pack* Here we are! My secret blend of peppers always does the trick, never fails, no not once. These'll fill you up much faster than that tripe they sell in the market!",
	[1075558] = L"Ah, you're missin' out my friend, you're missing out. My peppercorn fishsteaks are famous on this little isle of ours!",
	[502080] = L"Thank you for participating.  Your thoughts are important to us.",
	[1075556] = L"Ello there, looking for a good place on the dock to fish? I like the southeast corner meself. What's that? Oh, no, *sighs* me pole is broken and in for fixin'. My grandpappy gave me that pole, means a lot you see. Miss the taste of fish though... Oh say, since you're here, could you catch me a few fish? I can cook a mean fish steak, and I'll split 'em with you! But make sure it's one of the green kind, they're the best for seasoning!",
	[1075554] = L"<center>Spring Decor Collection Item</center>",
	[1075552] = L"A Cozy Life Starter Kit has been created in your bank box!",
	[502081] = L"Thank you for participating.  Your thoughts are important to us.",
	[1075550] = L"Cozy Life Starter Kit",
	[1075548] = L"Ha! Finally! I've had a rune to the waterfalls near Justice Isle that I've been wanting to use for the longest time, and now I can visit at last. Here's that book I promised you... glad to be rid of it, to be honest.",
	[1075546] = L"Hmm, thought I had your interest there for a moment. It's not everyday you see a book made from real daemon skin, after all!",
	[502082] = L"You will not be asked again about this poll.",
	[1075544] = L"Inscribe five 'Recall' scrolls",
	[1075542] = L"The Pen is Mightier",
	[1075540] = L"The scent of fresh herbs begins to fill your home...",
	[502083] = L"You will be given the chance to vote the next time you log in.",
	[1075538] = L"That's right, move it! I need sixty logs on the double, and they need to be freshly cut! If you can get them to me fast I'll have your payment in your hands before you have the scent of pine out from beneath your nostrils. Just get a sharp axe and hack away at some of the trees in the land and your lumberjacking skill will rise in no time.",
	[1075536] = L"Wonderful! Tick tock, tick tock, soon all shall be well with grandfather's clock!",
	[1075534] = L"'Tis a riddle, you see! \"What kind of clock is only right twice per day? A broken one!\" *laughs heartily* Ah, yes *wipes eye*, that's one of my favorites! Ah... to business. Could you fashion me some clock parts? I wish my own clocks to be right all the day long! You'll need some tinker's tools and some iron ingots, I think, but from there it should be just a matter of working the metal.",
	[502084] = L"Opening web browser for more details on Siege Perilous...",
	[1075532] = L"Hmmm\x2026 we need some more Ore. Try finding a mountain or cave, and give it a whack.",
	[1075530] = L"More Ore Please",
	[1075528] = L"It's gorgeous! I only have a few things to give you in return, but I can't thank you enough! Maybe I'll even catch Uzeraan's eye at the, er, *blushes* I mean, I can't wait to wear it to the next town dance!",
	[502085] = L"You have chosen to renounce your `Young' player status.",
	[1075526] = L"Won't you reconsider? It'd mean the world to me, it would!",
	[1075524] = L"an old ring",
	[1075522] = L"Oh how I wish I had a fancy dress like the noble ladies of Castle British! I don't have much... but I have a few trinkets I might trade for it. It would mean the world to me to go to a fancy ball and dance the night away. Oh, and I could tell you how to make one! You just need to use your sewing kit on enough cut cloth, that's all.",
	[502086] = L"You have chosen not to renounce your `Young' player status.",
	[1075520] = L"Are you sure you wish to leave this guided tour? You will not be able to return.",
	[1075518] = L"Hail friend, hast thou a moment? A mishap with a saw hath left me in a sorry state, for it shall be a while before I canst return to carpentry. In the meantime, I need a comfortable chair that I may rest. Could thou craft a straw chair?  Only a tool, such as a dovetail saw, a few boards, and some skill as a carpenter is needed. Remember, this is a piece of furniture, so please pay attention to detail.",
	[1075516] = L"Thanks for the help. Here's something for ya to remember me by.",
	[502087] = L"You have been ejected from this house!",
	[1075514] = L"Not enough muscle on yer bones to use it? hmph, probably afraid of the sparks markin' up yer loverly skin... to good for some honest labor... ha!... off with ya!",
	[1075512] = L"Hey there! Yeah... you! Ya' any good with a hammer? Tell ya what, if yer thinking about tryin' some metal work, and have a bit of skill, I can show ya how to bend it into shape. Just get some of ingots and a hammer and use it over here at this forge. You can always buy ingots at the market, but I highly suggest that you mine yer own. You can either make a smith's hammer yerself if ya have the tinkering skill, or buy it from a tinker at the market. I need a few more bucklers hammered out to fill this here order with...  hmmm about ten more. that'll give some taste of how to work the metal.",
	[1075510] = L"(20) Arrows",
	[502088] = L"A special gift has been placed in your backpack.",
	[1075508] = L"Oh. Well. I'll just keep trying alone, I suppose...",
	[1075506] = L"Split Ends",
	[1075504] = L"<U>Cancel Pending Request</U>: Remove my pending help request from the queue.",
	[502089] = L"You cannot be a member of the Thieves' Guild while you are Young.",
	[1075502] = L"Low Yew Table",
	[1075500] = L"Navigator's World Map",
	[1075498] = L"Mongbat Dartboard",
	[502090] = L"Click on the player whom you wish to honor.",
	[1075496] = L"Throw Pillow",
	[1075494] = L"Blessed Statue",
	[1075492] = L"Surveyor's Scope",
	[502091] = L"Your words fall silently to the floor.",
	[1075490] = L"Just remember you need to use your mortar and pestle while you have empty bottles and some black pearl. Refresh potions are what I need.",
	[1075488] = L"Help me! I am lost! You then, you an Alchemist? If you can make me a few Refresh potions, I will be back on my feet and can give those lizards the what for! Find a mortar and pestle, a good amount of black pearl, and ten empty bottles to store the finished potions in. Just use the mortar and pestle and the rest will surely come to you. When you return, the favor will be repaid.",
	[1075486] = L"I Shot an Arrow Into the Air...<br>",
	[502092] = L"You must be in your house to do this.",
	[1075484] = L"Return once ye have killed ten sheep with a bow and not a moment before.",
	[1075482] = L"Truth be told, the only way to get a feel for the bow is to shoot one and there's no better practice target than a sheep. If ye can shoot ten of them I think ye will have proven yer abilities. Just grab a bow and make sure to take enough ammunition. Bows tend to use arrows and crossbows use bolts. Ye can buy 'em or have someone craft 'em. How about it then? Come back here when ye are done.",
	[1075480] = L"Argh, I absolutely must have more of these 'cookies!' Come back if you change your mind.",
	[502093] = L"Your words fall silently to the floor.",
	[1075478] = L"Baker's Dozen",
	[1075476] = L"Years ago, in a time before the Gem was shattered, we could have been friends and companions.<br>Now I am trapped by the very fragments of that destroyed promise while you are still free to roam the world.<br>We are not enemies, but you have what I seek. Your freedom shall become mine.<br>That is why I brought you across the shards when the opportunity arose.",
	[1075474] = L"Heartwood was not kept hidden, it has always been central to this world.<br>But methods of traveling into the heart of this tree were broken when the gem was shattered.<br>Heartwood is home to the Elves of Sosaria. Their culture is different, but we are learning to live together again.<br>Mostly.<br>You see, there remains a sect still loyal to Mondain.<br>They call themselves the Cult of the Fallen. <br>You may read more about them as you look further into the history of Britannia.",
	[502094] = L"You must be in your house to do this.",
	[1075472] = L"This is the Hedge Maze, or at least part of it.<br>It was built by Relvinian, a powerful, but mad magician who was fascinated by demons.<br>Some of his experiments are still alive, waiting for the next victim to reach the center of the maze.<br>Nobody is certain what happened to Relvinian. His disappearance remains a mystery to this day.<br>But enough of that.",
	[1075470] = L"This is Haven. See that forge over there? Most cities have at least one.<br>The blacksmiths here sell simple armor and weapons but you'll learn how to craft better versions.<br>One day you may decide to become a tailor or an alchemist or maybe even a renowned carpenter.<br>Your bank vault may not have enough room to hold all of your wares so you'll need something a bit larger to store your possessions.",
	[1075468] = L"Let me show you around your new home. <br>Look closely at the crystal ball before you.<br>It will transport you to places that will become part of your future. <br>I will remain with you only in spirit. <br>You may see others like yourself, but they will not be able to see you. <br>Ready to see Britannia?",
	[502095] = L"You must be in your house to do this.",
	[1075466] = L"Ah yes, you over there. Come here.<br>You seem a bit puzzled.<br>It happens to nearly everyone that comes through here. <br>You see, you've been here before. In a way we all came from this place. <br>Still puzzled? Let me explain further.",
	[1075464] = L"You already have as many of those as you need.",
	[1075462] = L"Wolf Slayer",
	[502096] = L"You must own the house to do this.",
	[1075460] = L"Rubies",
	[1075458] = L"Your character name is too short.",
	[1075456] = L"You are not allowed to damage this NPC unless your on the Guilty Quest",
	[502097] = L"Lock what down?",
	[1075454] = L"I cannot offer you the quest again.",
	[1075452] = L"Alchemist's Bandage",
	[1075450] = L"a snowy scene of The Blighted Grove",
	[502098] = L"You must be in your house to do this.",
	[1075448] = L"a snowy scene of The Citadel",
	[1075446] = L"a snowy scene of Wrong",
	[1075444] = L"a snowy scene of Khaldun",
	[502099] = L"You must own the house to do this.",
	[1075442] = L"a snowy scene of Destard",
	[1075440] = L"a snowy scene of Covetous",
	[1075438] = L"You can only drink from the goblet of celebration when its in your inventory.",
	[502100] = L"Choose the item you wish to release",
	[1075436] = L"Daemons",
	[1075434] = L"Transparent Heart",
	[1075432] = L"Go away and never come back.",
	[502101] = L"You must be in your house to do this.",
	[1075430] = L"Goblet of Celebration",
	[1075428] = L"Saved Honor",
	[1075426] = L"The name of the villain is Jack, you will find him over by the port.",
	[502102] = L"You must own the house to do this.",
	[1075424] = L"Deliver the bag of jewels to the loan shark.",
	[1075422] = L"Jack the Villain",
	[1075420] = L"Are you sure? You are very kind. Many of the monsters around here, when slain, are found to have jewels in their stomachs. From innocents they have eaten, no doubt.",
	[502103] = L"Choose the item you wish to secure",
	[1075418] = L"Gather them quickly. Who knows how long Derek has to live?",
	[1075416] = L"The Honor of the De Boors",
	[1075414] = L"There\x2019s all kinds of daemons you can kill. There are some near the hedge maze, and some really powerful ones in Dungeon Doom.",
	[502104] = L"You must be in your house to do this.",
	[1075412] = L"Sash of Might",
	[1075410] = L"Doughty Warriors",
	[1075390] = L"West",
	[502105] = L"You must own the house to do this.",
	[1075388] = L"North-East",
	[1075386] = L"South",
	[1075384] = L"Excellent! That\x2019s the old fighting spirit.",
	[502106] = L"Choose the item you wish to unsecure",
	[1075382] = L"Ah. I see. Never mind then.",
	[1075380] = L"Youngsters these days! Sorry, I didn\x2019t introduce myself. I\x2019m Kane, the Master of Arms for this city. This lot of trainees I got, they\x2019re not worth a bucket of sour spit. You know the invasion some years back? Well, some of these pups weren\x2019t even born then! What I need is an example, something that will put some steel into their spines. You seem pretty tough, what do you say to helping me out?",
	[1075378] = L"She said what? She thinks what of me? I . . . I can\x2019t believe it! All this time, I never knew how she truly felt. Thank you, my friend. I believe now I will be able to paint once again. Here, take this bleach. I was going to use it to destroy all of my works. Perhaps you can find a better use for it now.",
	[502107] = L"You must be in your house to do this.",
	[1075376] = L"Very well, then. If you will excuse me, I need to get ready.",
	[1075374] = L"Emilio painted this? It is absolutely wonderful! I used to love looking at his paintings, but I don\x2019t remember him creating anything like this before. Would you be so kind as to carry a letter to him? Fate may have it that I am to marry another, yet I am compelled to reveal to him that his love was not entirely unrequited.",
	[1075372] = L"I\x2019m sorry, I\x2019m getting ready to be married. I don\x2019t have time to . . . what\x2019s that you say?",
	[502108] = L"You are not a co-owner of this hosue.",
	[1075370] = L"Alright then, you have already helped me more than I deserved. I shall find someone else to undertake this task.",
	[1075368] = L"Finished! With the pigment I was able to create from the Prismatic Amber you brought me, I was able to complete my humble work. I should explain. Once, I loved a noble lady of gentleness and refinement, who possessed such beauty that I have found myself unable to love another to this day. But it was from afar that I admired her, for it is not for one so lowly as I to pay court to the likes of her. You have heard of the fair Thalia, Lady of Nujel'm? No? Well, she was my Muse, my inspiration, and when I heard she was to be married, I lost whatever pitiful talent I possessed. I felt I must compose a portrait of her, my masterpiece, or I would never be able to paint again. You, my friend, have helped me complete my work. Now I ask another favor of you. Will you take it to her as a wedding gift? She will probably reject it, but I must make the offer.",
	[1075366] = L"Thank you my friend . . . I know she is at peace, now. Here, keep the weapon. Most of its power is expended, but it remains somewhat potent against wolf-kind.",
	[502109] = L"Owners do not get a strongbox of their own.",
	[1075364] = L"I understand. I am no warrior, either. I suppose I shall have to wait here until one comes along.",
	[1075362] = L"I came to this place looking for a cure for my wife. But I\x2019m getting ahead of myself -- my wife was attacked by a werewolf, and survived. Now she has become a werewolf herself. My research has turned up nothing that would cure her affliction. *Sob* She begged me to end her suffering, but I cannot. She has removed herself to a remote part of Ice Island so that she does not endanger others. If I give you the means, will you go there, find her, and give her the mercy of a clean death? ",
	[1075360] = L"I knew it! See, it\x2019s just the color I needed! Look how it brings out the highlights of her wheaten tresses!",
	[502110] = L"You cannot place a strong box there!",
	[1075358] = L"Is there no one who can help a humble artist pursue his Muse?",
	[1075356] = L"Aargh! It\x2019s just not right! It doesn\x2019t capture the unique color of her hair at all! If only I had some Prismatic Amber. That would be perfect. They used to mine it in Malas, but alas, those veins ran dry some time ago. I hear it may have been found in the Prism of Light. Oh, if only there were a bold adventurer within earshot who would go to the Prism of Light and retrieve some for me!",
	[1075354] = L"Pieced together by ~1_NAME~",
	[502111] = L"This is not a valid location.",
	[1075352] = L"Running",
	[1075350] = L"Prancing",
	[1075348] = L"Sorry, I\x2019m not accepting commissions at the moment. What? You have the bandage I need from Leon? Thank you so much! But why didn\x2019t my son bring this to me himself? . . . Oh, no! You can't be serious! *sag* My Freddie, my son! Thank you for carrying out his last wish. Here -- I made this for my son, to give to him when he became a journeyman. I want you to have it.",
	[502112] = L"You already have a strongbox!",
	[1075346] = L"Well I\x2019m sorry to hear you say that. Without your help, I don\x2019t know if I can get these to Andros quickly enough to help him.",
	[1075344] = L"That is simply terrible. First Andros, and now his son. Well, let\x2019s make sure Frederic\x2019s sacrifice wasn\x2019t in vain. Will you take the bandages to his father? You can probably deliver them faster than I can, can\x2019t you?",
	[1075342] = L"How may I help thee? You have the silk of a dread spider? Of course I can make you a bandage, but what happened to Frederic?",
	[502113] = L"You cannot place a strongbox near a door or near steps.",
	[1075340] = L"Oh . . . that\x2019s your decision . . . OooOoooOOoo . . . ",
	[1075338] = L"My father, Andros, is a smith in Minoc. Last week his forge overturned and he was splashed by molten steel. He was horribly burned, and we feared he would die. An alchemist in Vesper promised to make a bandage that could heal him, but he needed the silk of a dread spider. I came here to get some, but I was careless, and succumbed to their poison. Please, won\x2019t you help my father?",
	[1075336] = L"A holiday sleigh",
	[502114] = L"You have a new strongbox. Only you and the houseowner may access this box.  You may place up to 25 items in the strongbox",
	[1075334] = L"A deed for a sleigh",
	[1075332] = L"Thank goodness! Now we can honor my father for the great man he was while he lived, rather than the horror he became.",
	[1075330] = L"You won\x2019t take this back to my daughter? Please, I cannot leave until she knows I am at peace.",
	[502115] = L"You must be in your house to do this.",
	[1075328] = L"You tell me it is time to leave this flesh. I did not understand until now. I thought: I can see my wife and my daughter, I can speak. Is this not life? But now, as I regard my reflection, I see what I have become. This only a mockery of life. Thank you for having the courage to show me the truth. For the love I bear my wife and daughter, I know now that I must pass beyond the veil. Will you return this basin to Aurelia? She will know by this that I am at rest.",
	[1075326] = L"What is this you give me? A basin of water?",
	[1075324] = L"Oh! Alright then. I hope someone comes along soon who can help me, or I don\x2019t know what will become of us.",
	[502116] = L"You must own the house to do this.",
	[1075322] = L"My father died in an accident some months ago. My mother refused to accept his death. We had a little money set by, and she took it to a necromancer, who promised to restore my father to life. Well, he revived my father, all right, the cheat! Now my father is a walking corpse, a travesty . . . a monster. My mother is beside herself -- she won't eat, she can't sleep. I prayed at the shrine of Spirituality for guidance, and I must have fallen asleep. When I awoke, there was this basin of clear water. I cannot leave my mother, for I fear what she might do to herself. Could you take this to the graveyard, and give it to what is left of my father?",
	[1075320] = L"A Crystal of Prismatic Amber",
	[1075318] = L"Raised by ~1_NAME~",
	[502117] = L"You already have a trash barrel!",
	[1075316] = L"He is dead, then? Good! I can think of no one more deserving. Thank you for your help. I feel that a great weight has been lifted from me. Here, I would like you to take this necklace. It belonged to my mother. She said it has some magic, but I have never been able to discover how it works. Perhaps you can.",
	[1075314] = L"Why? This man has killed many innocent people. Would you let him walk around, free?",
	[1075312] = L"I was born and raised in Buc\x2019s Den. Have you been there? Then you know what a lawless place it is. Five years ago, my mother and father were killed by brigands there. I was only a child, and so I was sent here to live with my uncle.<br>Recently, a man moved into town, and I\x2019m sure this man is the one who killed my parents. The sheriff will do nothing, he doesn\x2019t believe me. What can I do? I\x2019m no warrior. I can\x2019t use magic. I don\x2019t have the courage to avenge my family. Please, if you have any love at all for justice, I beg of you, seek out and slay this criminal!",
